obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6207)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6207&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Mental Healthcare Act,`
  line 2017.
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint; or on the date of completion of the period of nine months from the date on which the`
  line `Mental Healthcare Act, 2017 receives the assent of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 29th May, 2018, vide Notification No. S.O. 2173(E), dated 29th May 2018, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6208)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6208&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "advance directive" means an advance directive made by a person under section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) "appropriate Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a mental health establishment established, owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government or the Administrator of a Union territory having no legislature, the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a mental health establishment, other than an establishment referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (i), established, owned or controlled within the territory of--`
  line
  line `(A) a State, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(B) a Union territory having legislature, the Government of that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(c) "Authority" means the Central Mental Health Authority or the State Mental Health Authority,`
  line `as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(d) "Board" means the Mental Health Review Board constituted by the State Authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 80 in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) "care-giver" means a person who resides with a person with mental illness and is responsible for`
  line `providing care to that person and includes a relative or any other person who performs this function,`
  line `either free or with remuneration;`
  line
  line `(f) "Central Authority" means the Central Mental Health Authority constituted under`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(g) "clinical psychologist" means a person--`
  line
  line `(i) having a recognised qualification in Clinical Psychology from an institution approved and`
  line `recognised, by the Rehabilitation Council of India, constituted under section 3 of the Rehabilitation`
  line `Council of India Act, 1992 (34 of 1992); or`
  line
  line `(ii) having a Post-Graduate degree in Psychology or Clinical Psychology or Applied Psychology`
  line `and a Master of Philosophy in Clinical Psychology or Medical and Social Psychology obtained after`
  line `completion of a full time course of two years which includes supervised clinical training from any`
  line `University recognised by the University Grants Commission established under the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) and approved and recognised by the Rehabilitation Council of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (34 of 1992) or such recognised qualifications as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(h) "family" means a group of persons related by blood, adoption or marriage;`
  line
  line `(i) "informed consent" means consent given for a specific intervention, without any force, undue`
  line `influence, fraud, threat, mistake or misrepresentation, and obtained after disclosing to a person adequate`
  line `information including risks and benefits of, and alternatives to, the specific intervention in a language`
  line `and manner understood by the person;`
  line
  line `(j) "least restrictive alternative" or "least restrictive environment" or "less restrictive option"`
  line `means offering an option for treatment or a setting for treatment which--`
  line
  line `(i) meets the person's treatment needs; and`
  line
  line `(ii) imposes the least restriction on the person's rights;`
  line
  line `(k) "local authority" means a Municipal Corporation or Municipal Council, or Zilla Parishad, or`
  line `Nagar Panchayat, or Panchayat, by whatever name called, and includes such other authority or body`
  line `having administrative control over the mental health establishment or empowered under any law for the`
  line `time being in force, to function as a local authority in any city or town or village;`
  line
  line `(l) "Magistrate" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a metropolitan area within the meaning of clause (k) of section 2 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a Metropolitan Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other area, the Chief Judicial Magistrate, Sub-divisional Judicial Magistrate`
  line `or such other Judicial Magistrate of the first class as the State Government may, by notification,`
  line `empower to perform the functions of a Magistrate under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "medical officer in charge" in relation to any mental health establishment means the psychiatrist`
  line `or medical practitioner who, for the time being, is in charge of that mental health establishment;`
  line
  line `(n) "medical practitioner" means a person who possesses a recognised medical qualification--`
  line
  line `(i) as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956),`
  line `and whose name has been entered in the State Medical Register, as defined in clause (k) of that`
  line `section; or`
  line
  line `(ii) as defined in clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Indian Medicine Central Council`
  line `Act, 1970 (48 of 1970), and whose name has been entered in a State Register of Indian Medicine, as`
  line `defined in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of that section; or`
  line
  line `(iii) as defined in clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Homoeopathy Central Council`
  line `Act, 1973 (59 of 1973), and whose name has been entered in a State Register of Homoeopathy, as`
  line `defined in clause (i) of sub-section (1) of that section;`
  line
  line `(o) "Mental healthcare" includes analysis and diagnosis of a person's mental condition and treatment`
  line `as well as care and rehabilitation of such person for his mental illness or suspected mental illness;`
  line
  line `(p) "mental health establishment" means any health establishment, including Ayurveda, Yoga and`
  line `Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy establishment, by whatever name called, either wholly or`
  line `partly, meant for the care of persons with mental illness, established, owned, controlled or maintained by`
  line `the appropriate Government, local authority, trust, whether private or public, corporation, co-operative`
  line `society, organisation or any other entity or person, where persons with mental illness are admitted and`
  line `reside at, or kept in, for care, treatment, convalescence and rehabilitation, either temporarily or`
  line `otherwise; and includes any general hospital or general nursing home established or maintained by the`
  line `appropriate Government, local authority, trust, whether private or public, corporation, co-operative`
  line `society, organisation or any other entity or person; but does not include a family residential place where`
  line `a person with mental illness resides with his relatives or friends;`
  line
  line `(q) "mental health nurse" means a person with a diploma or degree in general nursing or diploma or`
  line `degree in psychiatric nursing recognised by the Nursing Council of India established under the Nursing`
  line `Council of India Act, 1947 (38 of 1947) and registered as such with the relevant nursing council in the`
  line State;
  line
  line `(r) "mental health professional" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a psychiatrist as defined in clause (y); or`
  line
  line `(ii) a professional registered with the concerned State Authority under section 55; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a professional having a post-graduate degree (Ayurveda) in Mano Vigyan Avum Manas`
  line `Roga or a post-graduate degree (Homoeopathy) in Psychiatry or a post-graduate degree (Unani) in`
  line `Moalijat (Nafasiyatt) or a post-graduate degree (Siddha) in Sirappu Maruthuvam;`
  line
  line `(s) "mental illness" means a substantial disorder of thinking, mood, perception, orientation or`
  line `memory that grossly impairs judgment, behaviour, capacity to recognise reality or ability to meet the`
  line `ordinary demands of life, mental conditions associated with the abuse of alcohol and drugs, but does not`
  line `include mental retardation which is a condition of arrested or incomplete development of mind of a`
  line `person, specially characterised by subnormality of intelligence;`
  line
  line `(t) "minor" means a person who has not completed the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(u) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression notify`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(v) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(w) "prisoner with mental illness" means a person with mental illness who is an under-trial or`
  line `convicted of an offence and detained in a jail or prison;`
  line
  line `(x) "psychiatric social worker" means a person having a post-graduate degree in Social Work and a`
  line `Master of Philosophy in Psychiatric Social Work obtained after completion of a full time course of two`
  line `years which includes supervised clinical training from any University recognised by the University`
  line `Grants Commission established under the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) or such`
  line `recognised qualifications, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(y) "psychiatrist" means a medical practitioner possessing a post-graduate degree or diploma in`
  line `psychiatry awarded by an university recognised by the University Grants Commission established under`
  line `the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956), or awarded or recognised by the National`
  line `Board of Examinations and included in the First Schedule to the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956`
  line `(102 of 1956), or recognised by the Medical Council of India, constituted under the Indian Medical`
  line `Council Act, 1956, and includes, in relation to any State, any medical officer who having regard to his`
  line `knowledge and experience in psychiatry, has been declared by the Government of that State to be a`
  line `psychiatrist for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(z) "regulations" means regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(za) "relative" means any person related to the person with mental illness by blood, marriage or`
  line adoption;
  line
  line `(zb) "State Authority" means the State Mental Health Authority established under section 45.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Medical`
  line `Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956) or the Indian Medicine Central Council Act, 1970 (48 of 1970) and not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6209)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Determination of mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6209&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Mental illness shall be determined in accordance with such`
  line `nationally or internationally accepted medical standards (including the latest edition of the International`
  line `Classification of Disease of the World Health Organisation) as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No person or authority shall classify a person as a person with mental illness, except for purposes`
  line `directly relating to the treatment of the mental illness or in other matters as covered under this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) Mental illness of a person shall not be determined on the basis of,—`
  line
  line `(a) political, economic or social status or membership of a cultural, racial or religious group, or for`
  line `any other reason not directly relevant to mental health status of the person;`
  line
  line `(b) non-conformity with moral, social, cultural, work or political values or religious beliefs prevailing`
  line `in a person's community.`
  line
  line `(4) Past treatment or hospitalisation in a mental health establishment though relevant, shall not by itself`
  line `justify any present or future determination of the person's mental illness.`
  line
  line `(5) The determination of a person's mental illness shall alone not imply or be taken to mean that the`
  line `person is of unsound mind unless he has been declared as such by a competent court.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6210)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Capacity to make mental healthcare and treatment decisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6210&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, including a`
  line `person with mental illness shall be deemed to have capacity to make decisions regarding his mental`
  line `healthcare or treatment if such person has ability to—`
  line
  line `(a) understand the information that is relevant to take a decision on the treatment or admission or`
  line `personal assistance; or`
  line
  line `(b) appreciate any reasonably foreseeable consequence of a decision or lack of decision on the`
  line `treatment or admission or personal assistance; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate the decision under sub-clause (a) by means of speech, expression, gesture or any`
  line `other means.`
  line
  line `(2) The information referred to in sub-section (1) shall be given to a person using simple language,`
  line `which such person understands or in sign language or visual aids or any other means to enable him to`
  line `understand the information.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person makes a decision regarding his mental healthcare or treatment which is perceived by`
  line `others as inappropriate or wrong, that by itself, shall not mean that the person does not have the capacity to`
  line `make mental healthcare or treatment decision, so long as the person has the capacity to make mental`
  line `healthcare or treatment decision under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6211)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6211&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, who is not a minor, shall have a right to make an advance`
  line `directive in writing, specifying any or all of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the way the person wishes to be cared for and treated for a mental illness;`
  line
  line `(b) the way the person wishes not to be cared for and treated for a mental illness;`
  line
  line `(c) the individual or individuals, in order of precedence, he wants to appoint as his nominated`
  line `representative as provided under section 14.`
  line
  line `(2) An advance directive under sub-section (1) may be made by a person irrespective of his past mental`
  line `illness or treatment for the same.`
  line
  line `(3) An advance directive made under sub-section (1), shall be invoked only when such person ceases to`
  line `have capacity to make mental healthcare or treatment decisions and shall remain effective until such person`
  line `regains capacity to make mental healthcare or treatment decisions.`
  line
  line `(4) Any decision made by a person while he has the capacity to make mental healthcare and treatment`
  line `decisions shall over-ride any previously written advance directive by such person.`
  line
  line `(5) Any advance directive made contrary to any law for the time being in force shall be ab initio void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6212)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Manner of making advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6212&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `An advance directive shall be made in the manner as may`
  line `be specified by the regulations made by the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6213)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Maintenance of online register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6213&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 91, every Board shall maintain an online register of all advance directives`
  line `registered with it and make them available to the concerned mental health professionals as and when`
  line required.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6214)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Revocation, amendment or cancellation of advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6214&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) An advance directive made`
  line `under section 6 may be revoked, amended or cancelled by the person who made it at any time.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for revoking, amending or cancelling an advance directive shall be the same as for`
  line `making an advance directive under section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6215)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Advance directive not to apply to emergency treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6215&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The advance directive shall not`
  line `apply to the emergency treatment given under section 103 to a person who made the advance directive.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6216)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty to follow advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6216&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every medical officer in charge of a`
  line `mental health establishment and the psychiatrist in charge of a person's treatment to propose or give`
  line `treatment to a person with mental illness, in accordance with his valid advance directive, subject to`
  line `section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6217)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to review, alter, modify or cancel advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6217&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a mental health`
  line `professional or a relative or a care-giver of a person desires not to follow an advance directive while`
  line `treating a person with mental illness, such mental health professional or the relative or the care-giver of`
  line `the person shall make an application to the concerned Board to review, alter, modify or cancel the`
  line `advance directive.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon receipt of the application under sub-section (1), the Board shall, after giving an opportunity`
  line `of hearing to all concerned parties (including the person whose advance directive is in question), either`
  line `uphold, modify, alter or cancel the advance directive after taking into consideration the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) whether the advance directive was made by the person out of his own free will and free from`
  line `force, undue influence or coercion; or`
  line
  line `(b) whether the person intended the advance directive to apply to the present circumstances,`
  line `which may be different from those anticipated; or`
  line
  line `(c) whether the person was sufficiently well informed to make the decision; or`
  line
  line `(d) whether the person had capacity to make decisions relating to his mental healthcare or`
  line `treatment when such advanced directive was made; or`
  line
  line `(e) whether the content of the advance directive is contrary to other laws or constitutional`
  line provisions.
  line
  line `(3) The person writing the advance directive and his nominated representative shall have a duty to`
  line `ensure that the medical officer in charge of a mental health establishment or a medical practitioner or a`
  line `mental health professional, as the case may be, has access to the advance directive when required.`
  line
  line `(4) The legal guardian shall have right to make an advance directive in writing in respect of a minor`
  line `and all the provisions relating to advance directive, mutatis mutandis, shall apply to such minor till such`
  line `time he attains majority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6218)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Review of advance directives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6218&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall regularly and periodically`
  line `review the use of advance directives and make recommendations in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Authority in its review under sub-section (1) shall give specific consideration to the`
  line `procedure for making an advance directive and also examine whether the existing procedure protects the`
  line `rights of persons with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Authority may modify the procedure for making an advance directive or make`
  line `additional regulations regarding the procedure for advance directive to protect the rights of persons with`
  line `mental illness.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6219)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Liability of medical health professional in relation to advance directive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6219&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A medical`
  line `practitioner or a mental health professional shall not be held liable for any unforeseen consequences on`
  line `following a valid advance directive.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical practitioner or mental health professional shall not be held liable for not following a`
  line `valid advance directive, if he has not been given a copy of the valid advance directive.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6220)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment and revocation of nominated representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6220&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 5, every person who is not a minor, shall have a`
  line `right to appoint a nominated representative.`
  line
  line `(2) The nomination under sub-section (1) shall be made in writing on plain paper with the person's`
  line `signature or thumb impression of the person referred to in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) The person appointed as the nominated representative shall not be a minor, be competent to`
  line `discharge the duties or perform the functions assigned to him under this Act, and give his consent in`
  line `writing to the mental health professional to discharge his duties and perform the functions assigned to`
  line `him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Where no nominated representative is appointed by a person under sub-section (1), the following`
  line `persons for the purposes of this Act in the order of precedence shall be deemed to be the nominated`
  line `representative of a person with mental illness, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the individual appointed as the nominated representative in the advance directive under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 5; or`
  line
  line `(b) a relative, or if not available or not willing to be the nominated representative of such person;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) a care-giver, or if not available or not willing to be the nominated representative of such`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(d) a suitable person appointed as such by the concerned Board; or`
  line
  line `(e) if no such person is available to be appointed as a nominated representative, the Board shall`
  line `appoint the Director, Department of Social Welfare, or his designated representative, as the`
  line `nominated representative of the person with mental illness:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person representing an organisation registered under the Societies Registration Act,`
  line `1860 (21 of 1860) or any other law for the time being in force, working for persons with mental illness,`
  line `may temporarily be engaged by the mental health professional to discharge the duties of a nominated`
  line `representative pending appointment of a nominated representative by the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The representative of the organisation, referred to in the proviso to sub-section (4), may make a`
  line `written application to the medical officer in-charge of the mental health establishment or the psychiatrist`
  line `in-charge of the person's treatment, and such medical officer or psychiatrist, as the case may be, shall`
  line `accept him as the temporary nominated representative, pending appointment of a nominated`
  line `representative by the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(6) A person who has appointed any person as his nominated representative under this section may`
  line `revoke or alter such appointment at any time in accordance with the procedure laid down for making an`
  line `appointment of nominated representative under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) The Board may, if it is of the opinion that it is in the interest of the person with mental illness to`
  line `do so, revoke an appointment made by it under this section, and appoint a different representative under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(8) The appointment of a nominated representative, or the inability of a person with mental illness to`
  line `appoint a nominated representative, shall not be construed as the lack of capacity of the person to take`
  line `decisions about his mental healthcare or treatment.`
  line
  line `(9) All persons with mental illness shall have capacity to make mental healthcare or treatment`
  line `decisions but may require varying levels of support from their nominated representative to make`
  line decisions.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6221)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Nominated representative of minor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6221&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 14, in`
  line `case of minors, the legal guardian shall be their nominated representative, unless the concerned Board`
  line `orders otherwise under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Where on an application made to the concerned Board, by a mental health professional or any`
  line `other person acting in the best interest of the minor, and on evidence presented before it, the concerned`
  line `Board is of the opinion that,—`
  line
  line `(a) the legal guardian is not acting in the best interests of the minor; or`
  line
  line `(b) the legal guardian is otherwise not fit to act as the nominated representative of the minor,`
  line
  line `it may appoint, any suitable individual who is willing to act as such, the nominated representative of the`
  line `minor with mental illness:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case no individual is available for appointment as a nominated representative, the`
  line `Board shall appoint the Director in the Department of Social Welfare of the State in which such Board is`
  line `located, or his nominee, as the nominated representative of the minor with mental illness..`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6222)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Revocation, alteration, etc., of nominated representative by Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6222&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Board, on an`
  line `application made to it by the person with mental illness, or by a relative of such person, or by the`
  line `psychiatrist responsible for the care of such person, or by the medical officer in-charge of the mental`
  line `health establishment where the individual is admitted or proposed to be admitted, may revoke, alter or`
  line `modify the order made under clause (e) of sub-section (4) of section 14 or under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6223)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duties of nominated representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6223&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `While fulfilling his duties under this Act, the nominated`
  line `representative shall—`
  line
  line `(a) consider the current and past wishes, the life history, values, cultural background and the best`
  line `interests of the person with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(b) give particular credence to the views of the person with mental illness to the extent that the`
  line `person understands the nature of the decisions under consideration;`
  line
  line `(c) provide support to the person with mental illness in making treatment decisions under`
  line `section 89 or section 90;`
  line
  line `(d) have right to seek information on diagnosis and treatment to provide adequate support to the`
  line `person with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(e) have access to the family or home based rehabilitation services as provided under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 18 on behalf of and for the benefit of the person with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(f) be involved in discharge planning under section 98;`
  line
  line `(g) apply to the mental health establishment for admission under section 87 or section 89 or`
  line `section 90;`
  line
  line `(h) apply to the concerned Board on behalf of the person with mental illness for discharge under`
  line `section 87 or section 89 or section 90;`
  line
  line `(i) apply to the concerned Board against violation of rights of the person with mental illness in a`
  line `mental health establishment;`
  line
  line `(j) appoint a suitable attendant under sub-section (5) or sub-section (6) of section 87;`
  line
  line `(k) have the right to give or withhold consent for research under circumstances mentioned under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 99.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6224)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Right to access mental healthcare.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6224&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person shall have a right to access mental`
  line `healthcare and treatment from mental health services run or funded by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The right to access mental healthcare and treatment shall mean mental health services of`
  line `affordable cost, of good quality, available in sufficient quantity, accessible geographically, without`
  line `discrimination on the basis of gender, sex, sexual orientation, religion, culture, caste, social or political`
  line `beliefs, class, disability or any other basis and provided in a manner that is acceptable to persons with`
  line `mental illness and their families and care-givers.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall make sufficient provision as may be necessary, for a range of`
  line `services required by persons with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the generality of range of services under sub-section (3), such services shall`
  line include—
  line
  line `(a) provision of acute mental healthcare services such as outpatient and inpatient services;`
  line
  line `(b) provision of half-way homes, sheltered accommodation, supported accommodation as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) provision for mental health services to support family of person with mental illness or home`
  line `based rehabilitation;`
  line
  line `(d) hospital and community based rehabilitation establishments and services as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(e) provision for child mental health services and old age mental health services.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) integrate mental health services into general healthcare services at all levels of healthcare`
  line `including primary, secondary and tertiary healthcare and in all health programmes run by the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(b) provide treatment in a manner, which supports persons with mental illness to live in the`
  line `community and with their families;`
  line
  line `(c) ensure that the long term care in a mental health establishment for treatment of mental illness`
  line `shall be used only in exceptional circumstances, for as short a duration as possible, and only as a last`
  line `resort when appropriate community based treatment has been tried and shown to have failed;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure that no person with mental illness (including children and older persons) shall be`
  line `required to travel long distances to access mental health services and such services shall be available`
  line `close to a place where a person with mental illness resides;`
  line
  line `(e) ensure that as a minimum, mental health services run or funded by Government shall be`
  line `available in each district;`
  line
  line `(f) ensure, if minimum mental health services specified under sub-clause (e) of sub-section are`
  line `not available in the district where a person with mental illness resides, that the person with mental`
  line `illness is entitled to access any other mental health service in the district and the costs of treatment at`
  line `such establishments in that district will be borne by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time the services under this sub-section are made available in a health`
  line `establishment run or funded by the appropriate Government, the appropriate Government shall make`
  line `rules regarding reimbursement of costs of treatment at such mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(6) The appropriate Government shall make available a range of appropriate mental health services`
  line `specified under sub-section (4) of section 18 at all general hospitals run or funded by such Government`
  line `and basic and emergency mental healthcare services shall be available at all community health centres`
  line `and upwards in the public health system run or funded by such Government.`
  line
  line `(7) Persons with mental illness living below the poverty line whether or not in possession of a below`
  line `poverty line card, or who are destitute or homeless shall be entitled to mental health treatment and`
  line `services free of any charge and at no financial cost at all mental health establishments run or funded by`
  line `the appropriate Government and at other mental health establishments designated by it.`
  line
  line `(8) The appropriate Government shall ensure that the mental health services shall be of equal quality`
  line `to other general health services and no discrimination be made in quality of services provided to persons`
  line `with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(9) The minimum quality standards of mental health services shall be as specified by regulations`
  line `made by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(10) Without prejudice to the generality of range of services under sub-section (3) of section 18, the`
  line `appropriate Government shall notify Essential Drug List and all medicines on the Essential Drug List`
  line `shall be made available free of cost to all persons with mental illness at all times at health`
  line `establishments run or funded by the appropriate Government starting from Community Health Centres`
  line `and upwards in the public health system:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the health professional of ayurveda, yoga, unani, siddha, homoeopathy or`
  line `naturopathy systems recognised by the Central Government are available in any health establishment,`
  line `the essential medicines from any similar list relating to the appropriate ayurveda, yoga, unani, siddha,`
  line `homoeopathy or naturopathy systems shall also be made available free of cost to all persons with mental`
  line illness.
  line
  line `(11) The appropriate Government shall take measures to ensure that necessary budgetary provisions`
  line `in terms of adequacy, priority, progress and equity are made for effective implementation of the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of sub-section (11), the expressions—`
  line
  line `(i) "adequacy" means in terms of how much is enough to offset inflation;`
  line
  line `(ii) "priority" means in terms of compared to other budget heads;`
  line
  line `(iii) "equity" means in terms of fair allocation of resources taking into account the health, social`
  line `and economic burden of mental illness on individuals, their families and care-givers;`
  line
  line `(iv) "progress" means in terms of indicating an improvement in the State's response.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (6225)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Right to community living.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6225&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person with mental illness shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) have a right to live in, be part of and not be segregated from society; and`
  line
  line `(b) not continue to remain in a mental health establishment merely because he does not have a`
  line `family or is not accepted by his family or is homeless or due to absence of community based`
  line facilities.
  line
  line `(2) Where it is not possible for a mentally ill person to live with his family or relatives, or where a`
  line `mentally ill person has been abandoned by his family or relatives, the appropriate Government shall`
  line `provide support as appropriate including legal aid and to facilitate exercising his right to family home`
  line `and living in the family home.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall, within a reasonable period, provide for or support the`
  line `establishment of less restrictive community based establishments including half-way homes, group`
  line `homes and the like for persons who no longer require treatment in more restrictive mental health`
  line `establishments such as long stay mental hospitals.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (6226)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right to protection from cruel, inhuman and degrading treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6226&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person with`
  line `mental illness shall have a right to live with dignity.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person with mental illness shall be protected from cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment`
  line `in any mental health establishment and shall have the following rights, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to live in safe and hygienic environment;`
  line
  line `(b) to have adequate sanitary conditions;`
  line
  line `(c) to have reasonable facilities for leisure, recreation, education and religious practices;`
  line
  line `(d) to privacy;`
  line
  line `(e) for proper clothing so as to protect such person from exposure of his body to maintain his`
  line dignity;
  line
  line `(f) to not be forced to undertake work in a mental health establishment and to receive appropriate`
  line `remuneration for work when undertaken;`
  line
  line `(g) to have adequate provision for preparing for living in the community;`
  line
  line `(h) to have adequate provision for wholesome food, sanitation, space and access to articles of`
  line `personal hygiene, in particular, women's personal hygiene be adequately addressed by providing`
  line `access to items that may be required during menstruation;`
  line
  line `(i) to not be subject to compulsory tonsuring (shaving of head hair);`
  line
  line `(j) to wear own personal clothes if so wished and to not be forced to wear uniforms provided by`
  line `the establishment; and`
  line
  line `(k) to be protected from all forms of physical, verbal, emotional and sexual abuse.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (6227)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Right to equality and non-discrimination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6227&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person with mental illness shall be treated`
  line `as equal to persons with physical illness in the provision of all healthcare which shall include the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be no discrimination on any basis including gender, sex, sexual orientation, religion,`
  line `culture, caste, social or political beliefs, class or disability;`
  line
  line `(b) emergency facilities and emergency services for mental illness shall be of the same quality and`
  line `availability as those provided to persons with physical illness;`
  line
  line `(c) persons with mental illness shall be entitled to the use of ambulance services in the same manner,`
  line `extent and quality as provided to persons with physical illness;`
  line
  line `(d) living conditions in health establishments shall be of the same manner, extent and quality as`
  line `provided to persons with physical illness; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other health services provided to persons with physical illness shall be provided in same`
  line `manner, extent and quality to persons with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(2) A child under the age of three years of a woman receiving care, treatment or rehabilitation at a`
  line `mental health establishment shall ordinarily not be separated from her during her stay in such establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the treating Psychiatrist, based on his examination of the woman, and if appropriate,`
  line `on information provided by others, is of the opinion that there is risk of harm to the child from the woman`
  line `due to her mental illness or it is in the interest and safety of the child, the child shall be temporarily`
  line `separated from the woman during her stay at the mental health establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the woman shall continue to have access to the child under such supervision of the`
  line `staff of the establishment or her family, as may be appropriate, during the period of separation.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision to separate the woman from her child shall be reviewed every fifteen days during the`
  line `woman's stay in the mental health establishment and separation shall be terminated as soon as conditions`
  line `which required the separation no longer exist:`
  line
  line `Provided that any separation permitted as per the assessment of a mental health professional, if it`
  line `exceeds thirty days at a stretch, shall be required to be approved by the respective Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) Every insurer shall make provision for medical insurance for treatment of mental illness on the same`
  line `basis as is available for treatment of physical illness.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (6228)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Right to information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6228&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness and his nominated representative shall`
  line `have the rights to the following information, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the provision of this Act or any other law for the time being in force under which he has been`
  line `admitted, if he is being admitted, and the criteria for admission under that provision;`
  line
  line `(b) of his right to make an application to the concerned Board for a review of the admission;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature of the person's mental illness and the proposed treatment plan which includes`
  line `information about treatment proposed and the known side effects of the proposed treatment;`
  line
  line `(d) receive the information in a language and form that such person receiving the information can`
  line understand.
  line
  line `(2) In case complete information cannot be given to the person with mental illness at the time of the`
  line `admission or the start of treatment, it shall be the duty of the medical officer or psychiatrist in-charge of the`
  line `person's care to ensure that full information is provided promptly when the individual is in a position to`
  line `receive it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the information has not been given to the person with mental illness at the time of`
  line `the admission or the start of treatment, the medical officer or psychiatrist in charge of the person's care shall`
  line `give the information to the nominated representative immediately.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (6229)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Right to confidentiality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6229&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness shall have the right to confidentiality`
  line `in respect of his mental health, mental healthcare, treatment and physical healthcare.`
  line
  line `(2) All health professionals providing care or treatment to a person with mental illness shall have a`
  line `duty to keep all such information confidential which has been obtained during care or treatment with the`
  line `following exceptions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) release of information to the nominated representative to enable him to fulfil his duties under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) release of information to other mental health professionals and other health professionals to`
  line `enable them to provide care and treatment to the person with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(c) release of information if it is necessary to protect any other person from harm or violence;`
  line
  line `(d) only such information that is necessary to protect against the harm identified shall be released;`
  line
  line `(e) release only such information as is necessary to prevent threat to life;`
  line
  line `(f) release of information upon an order by concerned Board or the Central Authority or High`
  line `Court or Supreme Court or any other statutory authority competent to do so; and`
  line
  line `(g) release of information in the interests of public safety and security.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (6230)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Restriction on release of information in respect of mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6230&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) No photograph or any`
  line `other information relating to a person with mental illness undergoing treatment at a mental health`
  line `establishment shall be released to the media without the consent of the person with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(2) The right to confidentiality of person with mental illness shall also apply to all information stored`
  line `in electronic or digital format in real or virtual space.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (6231)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Right to access medical records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6231&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) All persons with mental illness shall have the right to`
  line `access their basic medical records as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The mental health professional in charge of such records may withhold specific information in`
  line `the medical records if disclosure would result in,—`
  line
  line `(a) serious mental harm to the person with mental illness; or`
  line
  line `(b) likelihood of harm to other persons.`
  line
  line `(3) When any information in the medical records is withheld from the person, the mental health`
  line `professional shall inform the person with mental illness of his right to apply to the concerned Board for`
  line `an order to release such information.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (6232)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Right to personal contacts and communication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6232&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness admitted to`
  line `a mental health establishment shall have the right to refuse or receive visitors and to refuse or receive`
  line `and make telephone or mobile phone calls at reasonable times subject to the norms of such mental`
  line `health establishment.`
  line
  line `(2) A person with mental illness admitted in a mental health establishment may send and receive`
  line `mail through electronic mode including through e-mail.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person with mental illness informs the medical officer or mental health professional in`
  line `charge of the mental health establishment that he does not want to receive mail or e-mail from any`
  line `named person in the community, the medical officer or mental health professional in charge may restrict`
  line `such communication by the named person with the person with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) to (3) shall apply to visits from, telephone calls to, and`
  line `from mail or e-mail to, and from individuals, specified under clauses (a) to (f) under any circumstances,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) any Judge or officer authorised by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(b) members of the concerned Board or the Central Authority or the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) any member of the Parliament or a Member of State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(d) nominated representative, lawyer or legal representative of the person;`
  line
  line `(e) medical practitioner in charge of the person's treatment;`
  line
  line `(f) any other person authorised by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (6233)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Right to legal aid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6233&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness shall be entitled to receive free legal`
  line `services to exercise any of his rights given under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of magistrate, police officer, person in charge of such custodial institution as`
  line `may be prescribed or medical officer or mental health professional in charge of a mental health establishment to inform the person with mental illness that he is entitled to free legal services under the`
  line `Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987) or other relevant laws or under any order of the court`
  line `if so ordered and provide the contact details of the availability of services.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (6234)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Right to make complaints about deficiencies in provision of services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6234&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person with`
  line `mental illness or his nominated representative, shall have the right to complain regarding deficiencies in`
  line `provision of care, treatment and services in a mental health establishment to,—`
  line
  line `(a) the medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the establishment and if not`
  line `satisfied with the response;`
  line
  line `(b) the concerned Board and if not satisfied with the response;`
  line
  line `(c) the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions for making complaint in sub-section (1), is without prejudice to the rights of the`
  line `person to seek any judicial remedy for violation of his rights in a mental health establishment or by any`
  line `mental health professional either under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (6235)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Promotion of mental health and preventive programmes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6235&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government`
  line `shall have a duty to plan, design and implement programmes for the promotion of mental health and`
  line `prevention of mental illness in the country.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the appropriate`
  line `Government shall, in particular, plan, design and implement public health programmes to reduce`
  line `suicides and attempted suicides in the country.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (6236)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Creating awareness about mental health and illness and reducing stigma associated with mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6236&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall take all measures to ensure that,—`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act are given wide publicity through public media, including television,`
  line `radio, print and online media at regular intervals;`
  line
  line `(b) the programmes to reduce stigma associated with mental illness are planned, designed, funded`
  line `and implemented in an effective manner;`
  line
  line `(c) the appropriate Government officials including police officers and other officers of the`
  line `appropriate Government are given periodic sensitisation and awareness training on the issues under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (6237)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appropriate Government to take measures as regard to human resource development and training, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6237&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take measures to address the human resource`
  line `requirements of mental health services in the country by planning, developing and implementing`
  line `educational and training programmes in collaboration with institutions of higher education and training,`
  line `to increase the human resources available to deliver mental health interventions and to improve the`
  line `skills of the available human resources to better address the needs of persons with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall, at the minimum, train all medical officers in public healthcare`
  line `establishments and all medical officers in the prisons or jails to provide basic and emergency mental`
  line healthcare.
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall make efforts to meet internationally accepted guidelines for`
  line `number of mental health professionals on the basis of population, within ten years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (6238)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Co-ordination within appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6238&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall take all`
  line `measures to ensure effective co-ordination between services provided by concerned Ministries and`
  line `Departments such as those dealing with health, law, home affairs, human resources, social justice, employment, education, women and child development, medical education to address issues of mental`
  line `health care.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (6239)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Establishment of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6239&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, within a period of nine`
  line `months from the date on which this Act receives the assent of the President, by notification, establish,`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, an Authority to be known as the Central Mental Health Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (6240)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Composition of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6240&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary or Additional Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Health and`
  line `Family Welfare—chairperson ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Health and Family Welfare,`
  line `in charge of mental health—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Ayurveda, Yoga and`
  line `Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homeopathy—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Director General of Health Services—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Disability Affairs of the`
  line `Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Women and Child`
  line `Development—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) Directors of the Central Institutions for Mental Health—members ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) such other ex officio representatives from the relevant Central Government Ministries or`
  line Departments;
  line
  line `(i) one mental health professional as defined in item (iii) of clause (r) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government—member;
  line
  line `(j) one psychiatric social worker having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government—member;`
  line
  line `(k) one clinical psychologist having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be nominated`
  line `by the Central Government—member;`
  line
  line `(l) one mental health nurse having at least fifteen years experience in the field of mental health, to`
  line `be nominated by the Central Government—member;`
  line
  line `(m) two persons representing persons who have or have had mental illness, to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government—members;`
  line
  line `(n) two persons representing care-givers of persons with mental illness or organisations`
  line `representing care-givers, to be nominated by the Central Government—members;`
  line
  line `(o) two persons representing non-governmental organisations which provide services to persons`
  line `with mental illness, to be nominated by the Central Government—members;`
  line
  line `(p) two persons representing areas relevant to mental health, if considered necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The members referred to in clauses (h) to (p) of sub-section (1), shall be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (6241)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Term of office, salaries and allowances of chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6241&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of`
  line `the Central Authority referred to in clauses (h) to (p) of sub-section (1) of section 34 shall hold office as`
  line `such for a term of three years from the date of nomination and shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member shall not hold office as such after he has attained the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The chairperson and other ex officio members of the Authority shall hold office as such`
  line `chairperson or member, as the case may be, so long as he holds the office by virtue of which he is`
  line nominated.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `chairperson and other members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (6242)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6242&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `A member of the Central Authority may, by notice in writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his`
  line `office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such`
  line `notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon the office or until the expiry of his`
  line `term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (6243)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Filling of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6243&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, within two months from the date of`
  line `occurrence of any vacancy by reason of death, resignation or removal of a member of the Authority and`
  line `three months before the superannuation or completion of the term of office of any member of that`
  line `Authority, make nomination for filling up of the vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (6244)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6244&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Central Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person as a member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (6245)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Member not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6245&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any member having any direct or`
  line `indirect interest, whether pecuniary or otherwise, in any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting`
  line `of the Central Authority, shall, as soon as possible after the relevant circumstances have come to his`
  line `knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be recorded in`
  line `the proceedings of the Central Authority, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or`
  line `decision of the Authority with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (6246)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Officers and other employees of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6246&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a chief executive`
  line `officer of the Authority, not below the rank of the Director to the Government of India, to be appointed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, with the approval of the Central Government, determine the number, nature`
  line `and categories of other officers and employees required by the Central Authority in the discharge of its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service (including`
  line `the qualifications, experience and manner of appointment) of, the chief executive officer and other`
  line `officers and employees of the Central Authority shall be such as may be specified by regulations with`
  line `the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (6247)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Functions of chief executive officer of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6247&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The chief executive officer`
  line `shall be the legal representative of the Central Authority and shall be responsible for—`
  line
  line `(a) the day-to-day administration of the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) implementing the work programmes and decisions adopted by the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) drawing up of proposal for the Central Authority's work programmes;`
  line
  line `(d) the preparation of the statement of revenue and expenditure and the execution of the budget of`
  line `the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every year, the chief executive officer shall submit to the Central Authority for approval—`
  line
  line `(a) a general report covering all the activities of the Central Authority in the previous year;`
  line
  line `(b) programmes of work;`
  line
  line `(c) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line
  line `(d) the budget for the coming year.`
  line
  line `(3) The chief executive officer shall have administrative control over the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (6248)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6248&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `On the establishment of the Central`
  line Authority—
  line
  line `(a) all the assets and liabilities of the Central Authority for Mental Health Services constituted`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) shall stand transferred`
  line `to, and vested in, the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The assets of such Central Authority for Mental Health Services shall be deemed`
  line `to include all rights and powers, and all properties, whether movable or immovable, including, in`
  line `particular, cash balances, deposits and all other interests and rights in, or arising out of, such`
  line `properties as may be in the possession of such Unique Identification Authority of India and all books`
  line `of account and other documents relating to the same; and liabilities shall be deemed to include all`
  line `debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind;`
  line
  line `(b) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (a), all data and information collected during`
  line `enrolment, all details of authentication performed, debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all`
  line `contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for such Central`
  line `Authority for Mental Health Services immediately before that day, for or in connection with the`
  line `purpose of the said Central Authority for Mental Health Services, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for, the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums of money due to the Central Authority for Mental Health Services immediately`
  line `before that day shall be deemed to be due to the Central Authority; and`
  line
  line `(d) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against such Central Authority for Mental Health Services immediately before that day may be`
  line `continued or may be instituted by or against the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (6249)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Functions of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6249&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(a) register all mental health establishments under the control of the Central Government and`
  line `maintain a register of all mental health establishments in the country based on information provided`
  line `by all State Mental Health Authorities of registered establishments and compile update and publish`
  line `(including online on the internet) a register of such establishments;`
  line
  line `(b) develop quality and service provision norms for different types of mental health`
  line `establishments under the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) supervise all mental health establishments under the Central Government and receive`
  line `complaints about deficiencies in provision of services;`
  line
  line `(d) maintain a national register of clinical psychologists, mental health nurses and psychiatric`
  line `social workers based on information provided by all State Authorities of persons registered to work`
  line `as mental health professionals for the purpose of this Act and publish the list (including online on the`
  line `internet) of such registered mental health professionals;`
  line
  line `(e) train all persons including law enforcement officials, mental health professionals and other`
  line `health professionals about the provisions and implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) advise the Central Government on all matters relating to mental healthcare and services;`
  line
  line `(g) discharge such other functions with respect to matters relating to mental health as the Central`
  line `Government may decide:`
  line
  line `Provided that the mental health establishments under the control of the Central Government, before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, registered under the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, shall be deemed to have been registered under the provisions of this Act`
  line `and copy of such registration shall be furnished to the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for registration (including the fees to be levied for such registration) of the mental`
  line `health establishments under this section shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (6250)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Meetings of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6250&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall meet at such times (not less`
  line `than twice in a year) and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) as may be specified by regulations made`
  line `by the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If the chairperson, for any reason, is unable to attend a meeting of the Central Authority, the`
  line `senior-most member shall preside over the meeting of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes by the members present and voting and in the event of an equality of votes, the chairperson or`
  line `in his absence the member presiding over shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) All decisions of the Central Authority shall be authenticated by the signature of the chairperson`
  line `or any other member authorised by the Central Authority in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) If any member, who is a director of a company and who as such director, has any direct or`
  line `indirect pecuniary interest in any manner coming up for consideration at a meeting of the Central`
  line `Authority, he shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge,`
  line `disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be recorded in the`
  line `proceedings of the Authority, and the member shall not take part in any deliberation or decision of the`
  line `Authority with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (6251)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Establishment of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6251&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government shall, within a period of nine`
  line `months from the date on which this Act receives the assent of the President, by notification, establish,`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, an Authority to be known as the State Mental Health Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (6252)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Composition of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6252&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall consist of the following`
  line `chairperson and members:—`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary or Principal Secretary in the Department of Health of State Government—`
  line `chairperson ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Joint Secretary in the Department of Health of the State Government, in charge of mental`
  line `health—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Director of Health Services or Medical Education—member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Joint Secretary in the Department of Social Welfare of the State Government—member`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) such other ex officio representatives from the relevant State Government Ministries or`
  line Departments;
  line
  line `(f) Head of any of the Mental Hospitals in the State or Head of Department of Psychiatry at any`
  line `Government Medical College, to be nominated by the State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(g) one eminent psychiatrist from the State not in Government service to be nominated by the`
  line `State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(h) one mental health professional as defined in item (iii) of clause (r) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be nominated by the State`
  line Government—member;
  line
  line `(i) one psychiatric social worker having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be`
  line `nominated by the State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(j) one clinical psychologist having at least fifteen years experience in the field, to be nominated`
  line `by the State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(k) one mental health nurse having at least fifteen years experience in the field of mental health,`
  line `to be nominated by the State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(l) two persons representing persons who have or have had mental illness, to be nominated by the`
  line `State Government—member;`
  line
  line `(m) two persons representing care-givers of persons with mental illness or organisations`
  line `representing care-givers, to be nominated by the State Government—members;`
  line
  line `(n) two persons representing non-governmental organisations which provide services to persons`
  line `with mental illness, to be nominated by the State Government—members.`
  line
  line `(2) The members referred to in clauses (e) to (n) of sub-section (1), shall be nominated by the State`
  line `Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (6253)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Term of office, salaries and allowances of chairperson and other members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6253&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `members of the State Authority referred to in clauses (e) to (n) of sub-section (1) of section 46 shall`
  line `hold office as such for a term of three years from the date of nomination and shall be eligible for`
  line `reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member shall not hold office as such after he has attained the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The chairperson and other ex officio members of the State Authority shall hold office as such`
  line `chairperson or member, as the case may be, so long as he holds the office by virtue of which he is`
  line nominated.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `chairperson and other members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (6254)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6254&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `A member of the State Authority may, by notice in writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the State Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member shall, unless he is permitted by the State Government to relinquish his office`
  line `sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or`
  line `until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon office or until the expiry of his term of office,`
  line `whichever is the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (6255)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Filling of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6255&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, within two months from the date of`
  line `occurrence of any vacancy by reason of death, resignation or removal of a member of the Authority and`
  line `three months before the superannuation or completion of the term of office of any member of that`
  line `Authority, make nomination for filling up of the vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (6256)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6256&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the State Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the State Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person as a member of the State Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (6257)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Member not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6257&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Any member having any direct or`
  line `indirect interest, whether pecuniary or otherwise, in any matter coming up for consideration at a meeting`
  line `of the State Authority, shall, as soon as possible after the relevant circumstances have come to his`
  line `knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be recorded in`
  line `the proceedings of the State Authority, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or`
  line `decision of the State Authority with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (6258)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Officers and other employees of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6258&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a chief executive officer`
  line `of the State Authority, not below the rank of the Deputy Secretary to the State Government, to be`
  line `appointed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Authority may, with the approval of the State Government, determine the number,`
  line `nature and categories of other officers and employees required by the State Authority in the discharge of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service (including`
  line `the qualifications, experience and manner of appointment) of, the chief executive officer and other`
  line `officers and employees of the State Authority shall be such as may be specified by regulations with the`
  line `approval of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (6259)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Functions of chief executive officer of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6259&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The chief executive officer shall`
  line `be the legal representative of the State Authority and shall be responsible for—`
  line
  line `(a) the day-to-day administration of the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) implementing the work programmes and decisions adopted by the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) drawing up of proposal for the State Authority's work programmes;`
  line
  line `(d) the preparation of the statement of revenue and expenditure and the execution of the budget of`
  line `the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every year, the chief executive officer shall submit to the State Authority for approval—`
  line
  line `(a) a general report covering all the activities of the Authority in the previous year;`
  line
  line `(b) programmes of work;`
  line
  line `(c) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line
  line `(d) the budget for the coming year.`
  line
  line `(3) The chief executive officer shall have administrative control over the officers and other`
  line `employees of the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (6260)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6260&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `On and from the establishment of the State`
  line Authority—
  line
  line `(a) all the assets and liabilities of the State Authority for Mental Health Services constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) shall stand transferred to,`
  line `and vested in, the State Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The assets of such State Authority for Mental Health Services shall be deemed to`
  line `include all rights and powers, and all properties, whether movable or immovable, including, in`
  line `particular, cash balances, deposits and all other interests and rights in, or arising out of, such`
  line `properties as may be in the possession of such State Authority for Mental Health Services and all`
  line `books of account and other documents relating to the same; and liabilities shall be deemed to include`
  line `all debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind;`
  line
  line `(b) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (a), all data and information collected during`
  line `enrolment, all details of authentication performed, debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all`
  line `contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for such State`
  line `Authority for Mental Health Services immediately before that day, for or in connection with the`
  line `purpose of the said State Authority for Mental Health Services, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for, the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums of money due to the State Authority for Mental Health Services immediately before`
  line `that day shall be deemed to be due to the State Authority; and`
  line
  line `(d) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against such State Authority for Mental Health Services immediately before that day may be`
  line `continued or may be instituted by or against the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (6261)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Functions of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6261&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(a) register all mental health establishments in the State except those referred to in section 43 and`
  line `maintain and publish (including online on the internet) a register of such establishments;`
  line
  line `(b) develop quality and service provision norms for different types of mental health`
  line `establishments in the State;`
  line
  line `(c) supervise all mental health establishments in the State and receive complaints about`
  line `deficiencies in provision of services;`
  line
  line `(d) register clinical psychologists, mental health nurses and psychiatric social workers in the State`
  line `to work as mental health professionals, and publish the list of such registered mental health`
  line `professionals in such manner as may be specified by regulations by the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) train all relevant persons including law enforcement officials, mental health professionals and`
  line `other health professionals about the provisions and implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) discharge such other functions with respect to matters relating to mental health as the State`
  line `Government may decide:`
  line
  line `Provided that the mental health establishments in the State (except those referred to in section 43),`
  line `registered, before the commencement of this Act, under the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, shall be deemed to have been registered under the provisions`
  line `of this Act and copy of such registration shall be furnished to the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for registration (including the fees to be levied for such registration) of the mental`
  line `health establishments under this section shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (6262)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Meetings of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6262&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall meet at such times (not less than`
  line `four times in a year) and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) as may be specified by regulations made`
  line `by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If the chairperson, for any reason, is unable to attend a meeting of the State Authority, the seniormost`
  line `member shall preside over the meetings of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the State Authority shall be decided by a`
  line `majority of votes by the members present and voting and in the event of an equality of votes, the`
  line `chairperson or in his absence the member presiding over shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) All decisions of the State Authority shall be authenticated by the signature of the chairperson or`
  line `any other member authorised by the State Authority in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) If any member, who is a director of a company and who as such director, has any direct or`
  line `indirect pecuniary interest in any manner coming up for consideration at a meeting of the State`
  line `Authority, he shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have come to his knowledge,`
  line `disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be recorded in the proceedings of the Authority, and the member shall not take part in any deliberation or decision of the`
  line `State Authority with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (6263)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Grants by Central Government to Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6263&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after`
  line `due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Central Authority grants of`
  line `such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (6264)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Central Mental Health Authority Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6264&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the`
  line `Central Mental Health Authority Fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(i) any grants and loans made to the Authority by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) all fees and charges received by the Authority under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(iii) all sums received by the Authority from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund referred to in sub-section (1) shall be applied for meeting the salary, allowances and`
  line `other remuneration of the chairperson, other members, chief executive officer, other officers and`
  line `employees of the Authority and the expenses of the Authority incurred in the discharge of its functions`
  line `and for purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (6265)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Accounts and audit of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6265&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Authority shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the office of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon, shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government by the Authority and the Central Government shall cause`
  line `the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (6266)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Annual report of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6266&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The Central Authority shall prepare in every year, in`
  line `such form and at such time as may be prescribed by the Central Government, an annual report giving a`
  line `full account of its activities during the previous year, and copies thereof along with copies of its annual`
  line `accounts and auditor's report shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Central Government`
  line `shall cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
