obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (6271)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Registration of mental health establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6271&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person or organisation shall establish or`
  line `run a mental health establishment unless it has been registered with the Authority under the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "Authority" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the mental health establishments under the control of the Central Government,`
  line `the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of the mental health establishments in the State [not being the health establishments`
  line `referred to in clause (a)], the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person or organisation who proposes to establish or run a mental health establishment shall`
  line `register the said establishment with the Authority under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government, may, by notification, exempt any category or class of existing`
  line `mental health establishments from the requirement of registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In case a mental health establishment has been registered under the Clinical`
  line `Establishments (Registration and Regulation) Act, 2010 (23 of 2010) or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force in a State, such mental health establishment shall submit a copy of the said registration along`
  line `with an application in such form as may be prescribed to the Authority with an undertaking that the`
  line `mental health establishment fulfils the minimum standards, if any, specified by the Authority for the`
  line `specific category of mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall, on receipt of application under sub-section (2), on being satisfied that such`
  line `mental health establishment fulfils the standards specified by the Authority, issue a certificate of`
  line `registration in such form as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that till the period the Authority specifies the minimum standards for different categories of`
  line `mental health establishments, it shall issue a provisional certificate of registration to the mental health`
  line `establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that on specifying the minimum standards for different categories of mental health`
  line `establishments, the mental health establishment referred to in the first proviso shall, within a period of`
  line `six months from the date such standards are specified, submit to the Authority an undertaking stating`
  line `therein that such establishment fulfils the specified minimum standards and on being satisfied that such`
  line `establishment fulfils the minimum standards, the Authority shall issue a certificate of registration to`
  line `such mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(4) Every mental health establishment shall, for the purpose of registration and continuation of`
  line `registration, fulfil--`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum standards of facilities and services as may be specified by regulations made by`
  line `the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) the minimum qualifications for the personnel engaged in such establishment as may be`
  line `specified by regulations made by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) provisions for maintenance of records and reporting as may be specified by regulations made`
  line `by the Authority; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other conditions as may be specified by regulations made by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority may--`
  line
  line `(a) classify mental health establishments into such different categories, as may be specified by`
  line `regulations made by the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) specify different standards for different categories of mental health establishments;`
  line
  line `(c) while specifying the minimum standards for mental health establishments, have regard to local`
  line conditions.
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything in this section, the Authority shall, within a period of eighteen months`
  line `from the commencement of this Act, by notification, specify the minimum standards for different`
  line `categories of mental health establishments.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (6272)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Procedure for registration, inspection and inquiry of mental health establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6272&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mental health establishment shall, for the purpose of registration, submit an`
  line `application, in such form, accompanied with such details and fees, as may be prescribed, to the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The mental health establishment may submit the application in person or by post or online.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mental health establishment, existing on the date of commencement of this Act, shall,`
  line `within a period of six months from the date of constitution of the Authority, submit an application for its`
  line `provisional registration to the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall, within a period of ten days from the date of receipt of such application, issue`
  line `to the mental health establishment a certificate of provisional registration in such form and containing`
  line `such particulars and information as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority shall not be required to conduct any inquiry prior to issue of provisional`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall, within a period of forty-five days from the date of provisional registration,`
  line `publish in print and in digital form online, all particulars of the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(7) A provisional registration shall be valid for a period of twelve months from the date of its issue`
  line `and be renewable.`
  line
  line `(8) Where standards for particular categories of mental health establishments have been specified`
  line `under this Act, the mental health establishments in that category shall, within a period of six months`
  line `from date of notifying such standards, apply for that category and obtain permanent registration.`
  line
  line `(9) The Authority shall publish the standards in print and online in digital format.`
  line
  line `(10) Until standards for particular categories of mental health establishments are specified under this`
  line `Act, every mental health establishment shall, within thirty days before the expiry of the validity of`
  line `certificate of provisional registration, apply for a renewal of provisional registration.`
  line
  line `(11) If the application is made after the expiry of provisional registration, the Authority shall allow`
  line `renewal of registration on payment of such fees, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(12) A mental health establishment shall make an application for permanent registration to the`
  line `Authority in such form and accompanied with such fees as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(13) The mental health establishment shall submit evidence that the establishment has complied with`
  line `the specified minimum standards in such manner as may be specified by regulations by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(14) As soon as the mental health establishment submits the required evidence of the mental health`
  line `establishment having complied with the specified minimum standards, the Authority shall give public`
  line `notice and display the same on its website for a period of thirty days, for filing objections, if any, in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(15) The Authority shall, communicate the objections, if any, received within the period referred to`
  line `in sub-section (14), to the mental health establishment for response within such period as the Authority`
  line `may determine.`
  line
  line `(16) The mental health establishment shall submit evidence of compliance with the standards with`
  line `reference to the objections communicated to such establishment under sub-section (15), to the Authority`
  line `within the specified period.`
  line
  line `(17) The Authority shall on being satisfied that the mental health establishment fulfils the specified`
  line `minimum standards for registration, grant permanent certificate of registration to such establishment.`
  line
  line `(18) The Authority shall, within a period of forty-five days after the expiry of the period specified`
  line `under this section, pass an order, either—`
  line
  line `(a) grant permanent certificate of registration; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application after recording the reasons thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the Authority rejects the application under clause (b), it shall grant such period`
  line `not exceeding six months, to the mental health establishment for rectification of the deficiencies which`
  line `have led to rejection of the application and such establishment may apply afresh for registration.`
  line
  line `(19) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the Authority has neither communicated`
  line `any objections received by it to the mental health establishment under sub-section (15), nor has passed`
  line `an order under sub-section (18), the registration shall be deemed to have been granted by the Authority`
  line `and the Authority shall provide a permanent certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (6273)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Audit of mental health establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6273&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall cause to be conducted an audit`
  line `of all registered mental health establishments by such person or persons (including representatives of the`
  line `local community) as may be prescribed, every three years, so as to ensure that such mental health`
  line `establishments comply with the requirements of minimum standards for registration as a mental health`
  line establishment.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may charge the mental health establishment such fee as may be prescribed, for`
  line `conducting the audit under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority may issue a show cause notice to a mental health establishment as to why its`
  line `registration under this Act not be cancelled, if the Authority is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) the mental health establishment has failed to maintain the minimum standards specified by the`
  line `Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) the person or persons or entities entrusted with the management of the mental health`
  line `establishment have been convicted of an offence under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) the mental health establishment violates the rights of any person with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority may, after giving a reasonable opportunity to the mental health establishment, if`
  line `satisfied that the mental health establishment falls under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3), without prejudice to any other action which it may take against the mental health`
  line `establishment, cancel its registration.`
  line
  line `(5) Every order made under sub-section (4) shall take effect—`
  line
  line `(a) where no appeal has been preferred against such order, immediately on the expiry of the`
  line `period specified for preferring of appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the appeal has been preferred against such an order and the appeal has been dismissed,`
  line `from the date of the order of dismissal.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall, on cancellation of the registration for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `restrain immediately the mental health establishment from carrying on its operations, if there is`
  line `imminent danger to the health and safety of the persons admitted in the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(7) The Authority may cancel the registration of a mental health establishment if recommended by`
  line `the Board to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (6274)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Inspection and inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6274&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, suo motu or on a complaint received from any`
  line `person with respect to non-adherence of minimum standards specified by or under this Act or`
  line `contravention of any provision thereof, order an inspection or inquiry of any mental health`
  line `establishment, to be made by such person as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The mental health establishment shall be entitled to be represented at such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall communicate to the mental health establishment the results of such`
  line `inspection or inquiry and may after ascertaining the opinion of the mental health establishment, order`
  line `the establishment to make necessary changes within such period as may be specified by it.`
  line
  line `(4) The mental health establishment shall comply with the order of the Authority made under`
  line `sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) If the mental health establishment fails to comply with the order of the Authority made under`
  line `sub-section (3), the Authority may cancel the registration of the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority or any person authorised by it may, if there is any reason to suspect that any`
  line `person is operating a mental health establishment without registration, enter and search in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, and the mental health establishment shall co-operate with such inspection or`
  line `inquiry and be entitled to be represented at such inspection or inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (6275)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Appeal to High Court against order of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6275&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Any mental health establishment`
  line `aggrieved by an order of the Authority refusing to grant registration or renewal of registration or`
  line `cancellation of registration, may, within a period of thirty days from such order, prefer an appeal to the`
  line `High Court in the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `period of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (6276)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Certificates, fees and register of mental health establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6276&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every mental health`
  line `establishment shall display the certificate of registration in a conspicuous place in the mental health`
  line `establishment in such manner so as to be visible to everyone visiting the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(2) In case the certificate is destroyed or lost or mutilated or damaged, the Authority may issue a`
  line `duplicate certificate on the request of the mental health establishment and on the payment of such fees`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate of registration shall be non-transferable and valid in case of change of ownership`
  line `of the establishment.`
  line
  line `(4) Any change of ownership of the mental health establishment shall be intimated to the Authority`
  line `by the new owner within one month from the date of change of ownership.`
  line
  line `(5) In the event of change of category of the mental health establishment, such establishment shall`
  line `surrender the certificate of registration to the Authority and the mental health establishment shall apply`
  line `afresh for grant of certificate of registration in that category.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (6277)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Maintenance of register of mental health establishment in digital format.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6277&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The Authority`
  line `shall maintain in digital format a register of mental health establishments, registered by the Authority, to`
  line `be called the Register of Mental Health Establishments and shall enter the particulars of the certificate`
  line `of registration so granted in a separate register to be maintained in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (6278)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Duty of mental health establishment to display information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6278&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every mental health`
  line `establishment shall display within the establishment at conspicuous place (including on its website), the`
  line `contact details including address and telephone numbers of the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every mental health establishment shall provide the person with necessary forms to apply to the`
  line `concerned Board and also give free access to make telephone calls to the Board to apply for a review of`
  line `the admission.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (6279)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Constitution of Mental Health Review Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6279&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute Boards to be called the Mental Health Review Boards, for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The requisite number, location and the jurisdiction of the Boards shall be specified by the State`
  line `Authority in consultation with the State Governments concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) The constitution of the Boards by the State Authority for a district or group of districts in a State`
  line `under this section shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) While making rules under sub-section (3), the Central Government shall have regard to the`
  line `following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the expected or actual workload of the Board in the State in which such Board is to be`
  line constituted;
  line
  line `(b) number of mental health establishments existing in the State;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of persons with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(d) population in the district in which the Board is to be constituted;`
  line
  line `(e) geographical and climatic conditions of the district in which the Board is to be constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (6280)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Composition of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6280&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Board shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) a District Judge, or an officer of the State judicial services who is qualified to be appointed as`
  line `District Judge or a retired District Judge who shall be chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) representative of the District Collector or District Magistrate or Deputy Commissioner of the`
  line `districts in which the Board is to be constituted;`
  line
  line `(c) two members of whom one shall be a psychiatrist and the other shall be a medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `(d) two members who shall be persons with mental illness or care-givers or persons representing`
  line `organisations of persons with mental illness or care-givers or non-governmental organisations`
  line `working in the field of mental health.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be disqualified to be appointed as the chairperson or a member of a Board or be`
  line `removed by the State Authority, if he—`
  line
  line `(a) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which involves moral`
  line `turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(b) is adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a body corporate`
  line `owned or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(d) has such financial or other interest as is likely to prejudice the discharge of his functions as a`
  line `member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has such other disqualifications as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A chairperson or member of a Board may resign his office by notice in writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the Chairperson of the State Authority and on such resignation being accepted, the vacancy`
  line `shall be filled by appointment of a person, belonging to the category under sub-section (1) of section 74.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (6281)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Terms and conditions of service of chairperson and members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6281&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `chairperson and members of the Board shall hold office for a term of five years or up to the age of`
  line `seventy years, whichever is earlier and shall be eligible for reappointment for another term of five years`
  line `or up to the age of seventy years whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment of chairperson and members of every Board shall be made by the Chairperson`
  line `of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The honorarium and other allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of, the chairperson and members of the Board shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (6282)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Decisions of Authority and Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6282&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The decisions of the Authority or the Board, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be by consensus, failing which by a majority of votes of members present and voting`
  line `and in the event of equality of votes, the president or the chairperson, as the case may be, shall have a`
  line `second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(2) The quorum of a meeting of the Authority or the Board, as the case may be, shall be three`
  line members.
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (6283)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Applications to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6283&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person with mental illness or his nominated representative or`
  line `a representative of a registered non-governmental organisation, with the consent of such a person, being`
  line `aggrieved by the decision of any of the mental health establishment or whose rights under this Act have`
  line `been violated, may make an application to the Board seeking redressal or appropriate relief.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be no fee or charge levied for making such an application.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application referred to in sub-section (1) shall contain the name of applicant, his contact`
  line `details, the details of the violation of his rights, the mental health establishment or any other place where`
  line `such violation took place and the redressal sought from the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) In exceptional circumstances, the Board may accept an application made orally or over telephone`
  line `from a person admitted to a mental health establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (6284)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Proceedings before Board to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6284&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings before the Board shall`
  line `be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of sections 193, 219 and 228 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (6285)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6285&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be specified by regulations`
  line `made by the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (6286)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Proceedings before Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6286&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board, on receipt of an application under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 85, shall, subject to the provisions of this section, endeavour to hear and dispose of the same`
  line `within a period of ninety days.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall dispose of an application—`
  line
  line `(a) for appointment of nominated representative under clause (d) of sub-section (4) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) challenging admission of a minor under section 87;`
  line
  line `(c) challenging supported admission under sub-section (10) or sub-section (11) of section 89,`
  line
  line `within period of seven days from the date of receipt of such applications.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall dispose of an application challenging supported admission under section 90`
  line
  line `within a period of twenty-one days from the date of receipt of the application.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall dispose of an application, other than an application referred to in sub-section (3),`
  line `within a period of ninety days from the date of filing of the application.`
  line
  line `(5) The proceeding of the Board shall be held in camera.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall not ordinarily grant an adjournment for the hearing.`
  line
  line `(7) The parties to an application may appear in person or be represented by a counsel or a`
  line `representative of their choice.`
  line
  line `(8) In respect of any application concerning a person with mental illness, the Board shall hold the`
  line `hearings and conduct the proceedings at the mental health establishment where such person is admitted.`
  line
  line `(9) The Board may allow any persons other than those directly interested with the application, with`
  line `the permission of the person with mental illness and the chairperson of the Board, to attend the hearing.`
  line
  line `(10) The person with mental illness whose matter is being heard shall have the right to give oral`
  line `evidence to the Board, if such person desires to do so.`
  line
  line `(11) The Board shall have the power to require the attendance and testimony of such other witnesses`
  line `as it deems appropriate.`
  line
  line `(12) The parties to a matter shall have the right to inspect any document relied upon by any other`
  line `party in its submissions to the Board and may obtain copies of the same.`
  line
  line `(13) The Board shall, within five days of the completion of the hearing, communicate its decision to`
  line `the parties in writing.`
  line
  line `(14) Any member who is directly or indirectly involved in a particular case, shall not sit on the Board`
  line `during the hearings with respect to that case.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (6287)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Central Authority to appoint Expert Committee to prepare guidance document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6287&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Authority shall appoint an Expert Committee to prepare a guidance document for medical`
  line `practitioners and mental health professionals, containing procedures for assessing, when necessary or`
  line `the capacity of persons to make mental health care or treatment decisions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every medical practitioner and mental health professional shall, while assessing capacity of a`
  line `person to make mental healthcare or treatment decisions, comply with the guidance document referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) and follow the procedure specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (6288)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6288&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the powers and`
  line `functions of the Board shall, include all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to register, review, alter, modify or cancel an advance directive;`
  line
  line `(b) to appoint a nominated representative;`
  line
  line `(c) to receive and decide application from a person with mental illness or his nominated`
  line `representative or any other interested person against the decision of medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of mental health establishment or mental health establishment under section`
  line `87 or section 89 or section 90;`
  line
  line `(d) to receive and decide applications in respect non-disclosure of information specified under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(e) to adjudicate complaints regarding deficiencies in care and services specified under`
  line `section 28;`
  line
  line `(f) to visit and inspect prison or jails and seek clarifications from the medical officer in-charge of`
  line `health services in such prison or jail.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it is brought to the notice of a Board or the Central Authority or State Authority, that a`
  line `mental health establishment violates the rights of persons with mental illness, the Board or the Authority`
  line `may conduct an inspection and inquiry and take action to protect their rights.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Board, in consultation with the Authority,`
  line `may take measures to protect the rights of persons with mental illness as it considers appropriate.`
  line
  line `(4) If the mental health establishment does not comply with the orders or directions of the Authority`
  line `or the Board or wilfully neglects such order or direction, the Authority or the Board, as the case may be,`
  line `may impose penalty which may extend up to five lakh rupees on such mental health establishment and`
  line `the Authority on its own or on the recommendations of the Board may also cancel the registration of`
  line `such mental health establishment after giving an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (6289)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Appeal to High Court against order of Authority or Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6289&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Any person or establishment`
  line `aggrieved by the decision of the Authority or a Board may, within a period of thirty days from such`
  line `decision, prefer an appeal to the High Court of the State in which the Board is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `period of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (6290)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6290&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, make to the Central`
  line `Authority grants of such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The grants referred to in sub-section (1) shall be applied for,—`
  line
  line `(a) meeting the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the chairperson, members, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) meeting the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the chairperson, members, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Boards; and`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses of the Central Authority and the Boards incurred in the discharge of their`
  line `functions and for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (6291)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Admission of person with mental illness as independent patient in mental health establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6291&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, "independent patient or an independent admission"`
  line `refers to the admission of person with mental illness, to a mental health establishment, who has the capacity to make mental healthcare and treatment decisions or requires minimal support in making`
  line decisions.
  line
  line `(2) All admissions in the mental health establishment shall, as far as possible, be independent`
  line `admissions except when such conditions exist as make supported admission unavoidable.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (6292)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Independent admission and treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6292&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who is not a minor and who`
  line `considers himself to have a mental illness and desires to be admitted to any mental health establishment`
  line `for treatment may request the medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the`
  line `establishment to be admitted as an independent patient.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such request under sub-section (1), the medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of the establishment shall admit the person to the establishment if the medical`
  line `officer or mental health professional is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) the person has a mental illness of a severity requiring admission to a mental health`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(b) the person with mental illness is likely to benefit from admission and treatment to the mental`
  line `health establishment;`
  line
  line `(c) the person has understood the nature and purpose of admission to the mental health`
  line `establishment, and has made the request for admission of his own free will, without any duress or`
  line `undue influence and has the capacity to make mental healthcare and treatment decisions without`
  line `support or requires minimal support from others in making such decisions.`
  line
  line `(3) If a person is unable to understand the purpose, nature, likely effects of proposed treatment and of`
  line `the probable result of not accepting the treatment or requires a very high level of support approaching`
  line `hundred per cent. support in making decisions, he or she shall be deemed unable to understand the`
  line `purpose of the admission and therefore shall not be admitted as independent patient under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) A person admitted as an independent patient to a mental health establishment shall be bound to`
  line `abide by order and instructions or bye-laws of the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(5) An independent patient shall not be given treatment without his informed consent.`
  line
  line `(6) The mental health establishment shall admit an independent patient on his own request, and shall`
  line `not require the consent or presence of a nominated representative or a relative or care-giver for`
  line `admitting the person to the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions contained in section 88 an independent patient may get himself`
  line `discharged from the mental health establishment without the consent of the medical officer or mental`
  line `health professional in charge of such establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (6293)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Admission of minor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6293&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) A minor may be admitted to a mental health establishment only after`
  line `following the procedure laid down in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The nominated representative of the minor shall apply to the medical officer in charge of a`
  line `mental health establishment for admission of the minor to the establishment.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon receipt of such an application, the medical officer or mental health professional in charge`
  line `of the mental health establishment may admit such a minor to the establishment, if two psychiatrists, or`
  line `one psychiatrist and one mental health professional or one psychiatrist and one medical practitioner,`
  line `have independently examined the minor on the day of admission or in the preceding seven days and`
  line `both independently conclude based on the examination and, if appropriate, on information provided by`
  line `others, that,—`
  line
  line `(a) the minor has a mental illness of a severity requiring admission to a mental health`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(b) admission shall be in the best interests of the minor, with regard to his health, well-being or`
  line `safety, taking into account the wishes of the minor if ascertainable and the reasons for reaching this`
  line decision;
  line
  line `(c) the mental healthcare needs of the minor cannot be fulfilled unless he is admitted; and`
  line
  line `(d) all community based alternatives to admission have been shown to have failed or are`
  line `demonstrably unsuitable for the needs of the minor.`
  line
  line `(4) A minor so admitted shall be accommodated separately from adults, in an environment that takes`
  line `into account his age and developmental needs and is at least of the same quality as is provided to other`
  line `minors admitted to hospitals for other medical treatments.`
  line
  line `(5) The nominated representative or an attendant appointed by the nominated representative shall`
  line `under all circumstances stay with the minor in the mental health establishment for the entire duration of`
  line `the admission of the minor to the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(6) In the case of minor girls, where the nominated representative is male, a female attendant shall be`
  line `appointed by the nominated representative and under all circumstances shall stay with the minor girl in`
  line `the mental health establishment for the entire duration of her admission.`
  line
  line `(7) A minor shall be given treatment with the informed consent of his nominated representative.`
  line
  line `(8) If the nominated representative no longer supports admission of the minor under this section or`
  line `requests discharge of the minor from the mental health establishment, the minor shall be discharged by`
  line `the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(9) Any admission of a minor to a mental health establishment shall be informed by the medical`
  line `officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment to the concerned`
  line `Board within a period of seventy-two hours.`
  line
  line `(10) The concerned Board shall have the right to visit and interview the minor or review the medical`
  line `records if the Board desires to do so.`
  line
  line `(11) Any admission of a minor which continues for a period of thirty days shall be immediately`
  line `informed to the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(12) The concerned Board shall carry out a mandatory review within a period of seven days of being`
  line `informed, of all admissions of minors continuing beyond thirty days and every subsequent thirty days.`
  line
  line `(13) The concerned Board shall at minimum, review the clinical records of the minor and may`
  line `interview the minor if necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (6294)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Discharge of independent patients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6294&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) The medical officer or mental health professional in`
  line `charge of a mental health establishment shall discharge from the mental health establishment any person`
  line `admitted under section 86 as an independent patient immediately on request made by such person or if`
  line `the person disagrees with his admission under section 86 subject to the provisions of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(2) Where a minor has been admitted to a mental health establishment under section 87 and attains`
  line `the age of eighteen years during his stay in the mental health establishment, the medical officer in`
  line `charge of the mental health establishment shall classify him as an independent patient under section 86`
  line `and all provisions of this Act as applicable to independent patient who is not minor, shall apply to such`
  line person.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a mental health professional may prevent`
  line `discharge of a person admitted as an independent person under section 86 for a period of twenty-four`
  line `hours so as to allow his assessment necessary for admission under section 89 if the mental health`
  line `professional is of the opinion that—`
  line
  line `(a) such person is unable to understand the nature and purpose of his decisions and requires`
  line `substantial or very high support from his nominated representative; or`
  line
  line `(b) has recently threatened or attempted or is threatening or attempting to cause bodily harm to`
  line `himself; or`
  line
  line `(c) has recently behaved or is behaving violently towards another person or has caused or is`
  line `causing another person to fear bodily harm from him; or`
  line
  line `(d) has recently shown or is showing an inability to care for himself to a degree that places the`
  line `individual at risk of harm to himself.`
  line
  line `(4) The person referred to in sub-section (3) shall be either admitted as a supported patient under`
  line `section 89, or discharged from the establishment within a period of twenty-four hours or on completion`
  line `of assessments for admission for a supported patient under section 89, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (6295)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Admission and treatment of persons with mental illness, with high support needs, in mental health establishment, up to thirty days (supported admission).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6295&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The medical officer or`
  line `mental health professional in charge of a mental health establishment shall admit every such person to`
  line `the establishment, upon application by the nominated representative of the person, under this section,`
  line if—
  line
  line `(a) the person has been independently examined on the day of admission or in the preceding`
  line `seven days, by one psychiatrist and the other being a mental health professional or a medical`
  line `practitioner, and both independently conclude based on the examination and, if appropriate, on`
  line `information provided by others, that the person has a mental illness of such severity that the person,--`
  line
  line `(i) has recently threatened or attempted or is threatening or attempting to cause bodily harm to`
  line `himself; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has recently behaved or is behaving violently towards another person or has caused or is`
  line `causing another person to fear bodily harm from him; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has recently shown or is showing an inability to care for himself to a degree that places`
  line `the individual at risk of harm to himself;`
  line
  line `(b) the psychiatrist or the mental health professionals or the medical practitioner, as the case may`
  line `be, certify, after taking into account an advance directive, if any, that admission to the mental health`
  line `establishment is the least restrictive care option possible in the circumstances; and`
  line
  line `(c) the person is ineligible to receive care and treatment as an independent patient because the`
  line `person is unable to make mental healthcare and treatment decisions independently and needs very`
  line `high support from his nominated representative in making decisions.`
  line
  line `(2) The admission of a person with mental illness to a mental health establishment under this section`
  line `shall be limited to a period of thirty days.`
  line
  line `(3) At the end of the period mentioned under sub-section (2), or earlier, if the person no longer meets`
  line `the criteria for admission as stated in sub-section (1), the patient shall no longer remain in the`
  line `establishment under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) On the expiry of the period of thirty days referred to in sub-section (2), the person may continue`
  line `to remain admitted in the mental health establishment in accordance with the provisions of section 90.`
  line
  line `(5) If the conditions under section 90 are not met, the person may continue to remain in the mental`
  line `health establishment as an independent patient under section 86 and the medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of the mental health establishment shall inform the person of his admission status`
  line `under this Act, including his right to leave the mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(6) Every person with mental illness admitted under this section shall be provided treatment after`
  line `taking into account,—`
  line
  line `(a) an advance directive if any; or`
  line
  line `(b) informed consent of the patient with the support of his nominated representative subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (7).`
  line
  line `(7) If a person with the mental illness admitted under this section requires nearly hundred per cent.`
  line `support from his nominated representative in making a decision in respect of his treatment, the`
  line `nominated representative may temporarily consent to the treatment plan of such person on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(8) In case where consent has been given under sub-section (7), the medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of the mental health establishment shall record such consent in the medical`
  line `records and review the capacity of the patient to give consent every seven days.`
  line
  line `(9) The medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment`
  line `shall report the concerned Board,—`
  line
  line `(a) within three days the admissions of a woman or a minor;`
  line
  line `(b) within seven days the admission of any person not being a woman or minor.`
  line
  line `(10) A person admitted under this section or his nominated representative or a representative of a`
  line `registered non-governmental organisation with the consent of the person, may apply to the concerned`
  line `Board for review of the decision of the medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the`
  line `mental health establishment to admit the person to the mental health establishment under this section.`
  line
  line `(11) The concerned Board shall review the decision of the medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of the mental health establishment and give its findings thereon within seven days`
  line `of receipt of request for such review which shall be binding on all the concerned parties.`
  line
  line `(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, it shall be the duty of the medical officer or`
  line `mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment to keep the condition of the`
  line `person with mental illness admitted under this section on going review.`
  line
  line `(13) If the medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment`
  line `is of the opinion that the conditions specified under sub-section (1) are no longer applicable, he shall`
  line `terminate the admission under this section, and inform the person and his nominated representative`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(14) Non applicability of conditions referred to in sub-section (13) shall not preclude the person with`
  line `mental illness remaining as an independent patient.`
  line
  line `(15) In a case, a person with the mental illness admitted under this section has been discharged, such`
  line `person shall not be readmitted under this section within a period of seven days from the date of his`
  line discharge.
  line
  line `(16) In case a person referred to in sub-section (15) requires readmission within a period of seven`
  line `days referred to in that sub-section, such person shall be considered for readmission in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 90.`
  line
  line `(17) If the medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment`
  line `is of the opinion that the person with mental illness admitted under this section in the mental health`
  line `establishment requires or is likely to require further treatment beyond the period of thirty days, then`
  line `such medical officer or mental health professional shall be duty bound to refer the matter to be`
  line `examined by two psychiatrists for his admission beyond thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (6296)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Admission and treatment of persons with mental illness, with high support needs, in mental health establishment, beyond thirty days (supported admission beyond thirty days).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6296&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a`
  line `person with mental illness admitted under section 89 requires continuous admission and treatment`
  line `beyond thirty days or a person with mental illness discharged under sub-section (15) of that section`
  line `requires readmission within seven days of such discharge, he shall be admitted in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical officer or mental health professional in charge of a mental health establishment,`
  line `upon application by the nominated representative of a person with mental illness, shall continue`
  line `admission of such person with mental illness, if—`
  line
  line `(a) two psychiatrists have independently examined the person with mental illness in the preceding`
  line `seven days and both independently conclude based on the examination and, on information provided`
  line `by others that the person has a mental illness of a severity that the person—`
  line
  line `(i) has consistently over time threatened or attempted to cause bodily harm to himself; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has consistently over time behaved violently towards another person or has consistently`
  line `over time caused another person to fear bodily harm from him; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has consistently over time shown an inability to care for himself to a degree that places`
  line `the individual at risk of harm to himself;`
  line
  line `(b) both psychiatrists, after taking into account an advance directive, if any, certify that admission`
  line `to a mental health establishment is the least restrictive care option possible under the circumstances;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) the person continues to remain ineligible to receive care and treatment as a independent`
  line `patient as the person cannot make mental healthcare and treatment decisions independently and`
  line `needs very high support from his nominated representative, in making decisions.`
  line
  line `(3) The medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment`
  line `shall report all admissions or readmission under this section, within a period of seven days of such`
  line `admission or readmission, to the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall, within a period of twenty-one days from the date of last admission or`
  line `readmission of person with mental illness under this section, permit such admission or readmission or`
  line `order discharge of such person.`
  line
  line `(5) While permitting admission or readmission or ordering discharge of such person under`
  line `sub-section (4), the Board shall examine—`
  line
  line `(a) the need for institutional care to such person;`
  line
  line `(b) whether such care cannot be provided in less restrictive settings based in the community.`
  line
  line `(6) In all cases of application for readmission or continuance of admission of a person with mental`
  line `illness in the mental health establishment under this section, the Board may require the medical officer`
  line `or psychiatrist in charge of treatment of such person with mental illness to submit a plan for community`
  line `based treatment and the progress made, or likely to be made, towards realising this plan.`
  line
  line `(7) The person referred to in sub-section (4) shall not be permitted to continue in the mental health`
  line `establishment in which he had been admitted or his readmission in such establishment merely on the`
  line `ground of non-existence of community based services at the place where such person ordinarily resides.`
  line
  line `(8) The admission of a person with mental illness to a mental health establishment under this section`
  line `shall be limited to a period up to ninety days in the first instance.`
  line
  line `(9) The admission of a person with mental illness to a mental health establishment under this section`
  line `beyond the period of ninety days may be extended for a period of one hundred and twenty days at the`
  line `first instance and thereafter for a period of one hundred and eighty days each time after complying with`
  line `the provisions of sub-sections (1) to (7).`
  line
  line `(10) If the Board refuses to permit admission or continuation thereof or readmission under`
  line `sub-section (9), or on the expiry of the periods referred to in sub-section (9) or earlier if such person no`
  line `longer falls within the criteria for admission under sub-section (1), such person shall be discharged from`
  line `such mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(11) Every person with mental illness admitted under this section shall be provided treatment, after`
  line `taking into account—`
  line
  line `(a) an advance directive; or`
  line
  line `(b) informed consent of the person with the support from his nominated representative subject to`
  line `the provision of sub-section (12).`
  line
  line `(12) If a person with mental illness admitted under this section, requires nearly hundred per cent.`
  line `support from his nominated representative, in making decision in respect of his treatment, the nominated`
  line `representative may temporarily consent to the treatment plan of such person on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(13) In a case where consent has been given under sub-section (12), the medical officer or mental`
  line `health professional in charge of the mental health establishment shall record such consent in the medical`
  line `records of such person with mental illness and review on the expiry of every fortnight, the capacity of`
  line `such person to give consent.`
  line
  line `(14) A person with mental illness admitted under this section, or his nominated representative or a`
  line `representative of a registered non-governmental organisation with the consent of the person, may apply`
  line `to the concerned Board for review of the decision of the medical officer or mental health professional in`
  line `charge of medical health establishment to admit such person in such establishment and the decision of`
  line `the Board thereon shall be binding on all parties.`
  line
  line `(15) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the medical officer or mental health`
  line `professional in charge of the mental health establishment is of the opinion that the conditions under`
  line `sub-section (1) are no longer applicable, such medical officer or mental health professional shall`
  line `discharge such person from such establishment and inform such person and his nominated`
  line `representative accordingly.`
  line
  line `(16) The person with mental illness referred to in sub-section (15) may continue to remain in the`
  line `mental health establishment as an independent patient.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (6297)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Leave of absence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6297&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental`
  line `health establishment may grant leave to any person with mental illness admitted under section 87 or`
  line `section 89 or section 90, to be absent from the establishment subject to such conditions, if any, and for`
  line `such duration as such medical officer or psychiatrist may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (6298)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Absence without leave or discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6298&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `If any person to whom section 103 applies absents`
  line `himself without leave or without discharge from the mental health establishment, he shall be taken into`
  line `protection by any Police Officer at the request of the medical officer or mental health professional incharge`
  line `of the mental health establishment and shall be sent back to the mental health establishment`
  line immediately.
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (6299)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Transfer of persons with mental illness from one mental health establishment to another mental health establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6299&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness admitted to a mental health`
  line `establishment under section 87 or section 89 or section 90 or section 103, as the case may be, may`
  line `subject to any general or special order of the Board be removed from such mental health establishment`
  line `and admitted to another mental health establishment within the State or with the consent of the Central`
  line `Authority to any mental health establishment in any other State:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person with mental illness admitted to a mental health establishment under an order`
  line `made in pursuance of an application made under this Act shall be so removed unless intimation and`
  line `reasons for the transfer have been given to the person with mental illness and his nominated`
  line representative.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may make such general or special order as it thinks fit directing the`
  line `removal of any prisoner with mental illness from the place where he is for the time being detained, to`
  line `any mental health establishment or other place of safe custody in the State or to any mental health`
  line `establishment or other place of safe custody in any other State with the consent of the Government of`
  line `that other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (6300)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Emergency treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6300&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, any medical`
  line `treatment, including treatment for mental illness, may be provided by any registered medical`
  line `practitioner to a person with mental illness either at a health establishment or in the community, subject`
  line `to the informed consent of the nominated representative, where the nominated representative is`
  line `available, and where it is immediately necessary to prevent—`
  line
  line `(a) death or irreversible harm to the health of the person; or`
  line
  line `(b) the person inflicting serious harm to himself or to others; or`
  line
  line `(c) the person causing serious damage to property belonging to himself or to others where such`
  line `behaviour is believed to flow directly from the person's mental illness.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "emergency treatment" includes transportation of the`
  line `person with mental illness to a nearest mental health establishment for assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall allow any medical officer or psychiatrist to give to the person with`
  line `mental illness medical treatment which is not directly related to the emergency treatment specified`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall allow any medical officer or psychiatrist to use electro-convulsive`
  line `therapy as a form of treatment.`
  line
  line `(4) The emergency treatment referred to in this section shall be limited to seventy-two hours or till`
  line `the person with mental illness has been assessed at a mental health establishment, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that during a disaster or emergency declared by the appropriate Government, the period of`
  line `emergency treatment referred to in this sub-section may extend up to seven days.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (6301)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Prohibited procedures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6301&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the following`
  line `treatments shall not be performed on any person with mental illness—`
  line
  line `(a) electro-convulsive therapy without the use of muscle relaxants and anaesthesia;`
  line
  line `(b) electro-convulsive therapy for minors;`
  line
  line `(c) sterilisation of men or women, when such sterilisation is intended as a treatment for mental`
  line illness;
  line
  line `(d) chained in any manner or form whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if, in the opinion of psychiatrist in charge`
  line `of a minor's treatment, electro-convulsive therapy is required, then, such treatment shall be done with`
  line `the informed consent of the guardian and prior permission of the concerned Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (6302)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Restriction on psychosurgery for persons with mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6302&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, psychosurgery shall not be performed as a treatment for mental illness unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the informed consent of the person on whom the surgery is being performed; and`
  line
  line `(b) approval from the concerned Board to perform the surgery,`
  line `has been obtained.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Authority may make regulations for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (6303)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Restraints and seclusion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6303&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person with mental illness shall not be subjected to seclusion`
  line `or solitary confinement, and, where necessary, physical restraint may only be used when,--`
  line
  line `(a) it is the only means available to prevent imminent and immediate harm to person concerned or`
  line `to others;`
  line
  line `(b) it is authorised by the psychiatrist in charge of the person's treatment at the mental health`
  line establishment.
  line
  line `(2) Physical restraint shall not be used for a period longer than it is absolutely necessary to prevent`
  line `the immediate risk of significant harm.`
  line
  line `(3) The medical officer or mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment`
  line `shall be responsible for ensuring that the method, nature of restraint justification for its imposition and`
  line `the duration of the restraint are immediately recorded in the person's medical notes.`
  line
  line `(4) The restraint shall not be used as a form of punishment or deterrent in any circumstance and the`
  line `mental health establishment shall not use restraint merely on the ground of shortage of staff in such`
  line establishment.
  line
  line `(5) The nominated representative of the person with mental illness shall be informed about every`
  line `instance of restraint within a period of twenty-four hours.`
  line
  line `(6) A person who is placed under restraint shall be kept in a place where he can cause no harm to`
  line `himself or others and under regular ongoing supervision of the medical personnel at the mental health`
  line establishment.
  line
  line `(7) The mental health establishment shall include all instances of restraint in the report to be sent to`
  line `the concerned Board on a monthly basis.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Authority may make regulations for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(9) The Board may order a mental health establishment to desist from applying restraint if the Board`
  line `is of the opinion that the mental health establishment is persistently and wilfully ignoring the provisions`
  line `of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (6304)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Discharge planning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6304&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a person undergoing treatment for mental illness in a`
  line `mental health establishment is to be discharged into the community or to a different mental health`
  line `establishment or where a new psychiatrist is to take responsibility of the person's care and treatment, the`
  line `psychiatrist who has been responsible for the person's care and treatment shall consult with the person`
  line `with mental illness, the nominated representative, the family member or care-giver with whom the`
  line `person with mental illness shall reside on discharge from the hospital, the psychiatrist expected to be`
  line `responsible for the person's care and treatment in the future, and such other persons as may be`
  line `appropriate, as to what treatment or services would be appropriate for the person.`
  line
  line `(2) The psychiatrist responsible for the person's care shall in consultation with the persons referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) ensure that a plan is developed as to how treatment or services shall be provided to the`
  line `person with mental illness.`
  line
  line `(3) The discharge planning under this section shall apply to all discharges from a mental health`
  line establishment.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (6305)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title Research.
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6305&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) The professionals conducting research shall obtain free and informed consent`
  line `from all persons with mental illness for participation in any research involving interviewing the person`
  line `or psychological, physical, chemical or medicinal interventions.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of research involving any psychological, physical, chemical or medicinal interventions to`
  line `be conducted on person who is unable to give free and informed consent but does not resist participation`
  line `in such research, permission to conduct such research shall be obtained from concerned State Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Authority may allow the research to proceed based on informed consent being obtained`
  line `from the nominated representative of persons with mental illness, if the State Authority is satisfied`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) the proposed research cannot be performed on persons who are capable of giving free and`
  line `informed consent;`
  line
  line `(b) the proposed research is necessary to promote the mental health of the population represented`
  line `by the person;`
  line
  line `(c) the purpose of the proposed research is to obtain knowledge relevant to the particular mental`
  line `health needs of persons with mental illness;`
  line
  line `(d) a full disclosure of the interests of persons and organisations conducting the proposed research`
  line `is made and there is no conflict of interest involved; and`
  line
  line `(e) the proposed research follows all the national and international guidelines and regulations`
  line `concerning the conduct of such research and ethical approval has been obtained from the institutional`
  line `ethics committee where such research is to be conducted.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not restrict research based study of the case notes of a person`
  line `who is unable to give informed consent, so long as the anonymity of the persons is secured.`
  line
  line `(5) The person with mental illness or the nominated representative who gives informed consent for`
  line `participation in any research under this Act may withdraw the consent at any time during the period of`
  line research.
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (6306)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Duties of police officers in respect of persons with mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6306&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer`
  line `in-charge of a police station shall have a duty--`
  line
  line `(a) to take under protection any person found wandering at large within the limits of the police`
  line `station whom the officer has reason to believe has mental illness and is incapable of taking care of`
  line `himself; or`
  line
  line `(b) to take under protection any person within the limits of the police station whom the officer has`
  line `reason to believe to be a risk to himself or others by reason of mental illness.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer in-charge of a police station shall inform the person who has been taken into`
  line `protection under sub-section (1), the grounds for taking him into such protection or his nominated`
  line `representative, if in the opinion of the officer such person has difficulty in understanding those grounds.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person taken into protection under sub-section (1) shall be taken to the nearest public`
  line `health establishment as soon as possible but not later than twenty-four hours from the time of being`
  line `taken into protection, for assessment of the person's healthcare needs.`
  line
  line `(4) No person taken into protection under sub-section (1) shall be detained in the police lock up or`
  line `prison in any circumstances.`
  line
  line `(5) The medical officer in-charge of the public health establishment shall be responsible for`
  line `arranging the assessment of the person and the needs of the person with mental illness will be addressed`
  line `as per other provisions of this Act as applicable in the particular circumstances.`
  line
  line `(6) The medical officer or mental health professional in-charge of the public mental health`
  line `establishment if on assessment of the person finds that such person does not have a mental illness of a`
  line `nature or degree requiring admission to the mental health establishment, he shall inform his assessment`
  line `to the police officer who had taken the person into protection and the police officer shall take the person`
  line `to the person's residence or in case of homeless persons, to a Government establishment for homeless`
  line persons.
  line
  line `(7) In case of a person with mental illness who is homeless or found wandering in the community, a`
  line `First Information Report of a missing person shall be lodged at the concerned police station and the`
  line `station house officer shall have a duty to trace the family of such person and inform the family about the`
  line `whereabouts of the person.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (6307)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Report to Magistrate of person with mental illness in private residence who is ill-treated or neglected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6307&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer in-charge of a police station, who has reason to believe that any person`
  line `residing within the limits of the police station has a mental illness and is being ill-treated or neglected, shall forthwith report the fact to the Magistrate within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the person`
  line `with mental illness resides.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who has reason to believe that a person has mental illness and is being ill-treated or`
  line `neglected by any person having responsibility for care of such person, shall report the fact to the police`
  line `officer in-charge of the police station within whose jurisdiction the person with mental illness resides.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Magistrate has reason to believe based on the report of a police officer or otherwise, that`
  line `any person with mental illness within the local limits of his jurisdiction is being ill-treated or neglected,`
  line `the Magistrate may cause the person with mental illness to be produced before him and pass an order in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 102.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (6308)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Conveying or admitting person with mental illness to mental health establishment by Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6308&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person with mental illness or who may have a mental illness appears or is`
  line `brought before a Magistrate, the Magistrate may, order in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) that the person is conveyed to a public mental health establishment for assessment and`
  line `treatment, if necessary and the mental health establishment shall deal with such person in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) to authorise the admission of the person with mental illness in a mental health establishment`
  line `for such period not exceeding ten days to enable the medical officer or mental health professional in`
  line `charge of the mental health establishment to carry out an assessment of the person and to plan for`
  line `necessary treatment, if any.`
  line
  line `(2) On completion of the period of assessment referred to in sub-section (1), the medical officer or`
  line `mental health professional in charge of the mental health establishment shall submit a report to the`
  line `Magistrate and the person shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (6309)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Prisoners with mental illness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6309&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order under section 30 of the Prisoners Act, 1900`
  line `(3 of 1900) or under section 144 of the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or under section 145 of the`
  line `Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), or under section 143 or section 144 of the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957),`
  line `or under section 330 or section 335 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), directing the`
  line `admission of a prisoner with mental illness into any suitable mental health establishment, shall be`
  line `sufficient authority for the admission of such person in such establishment to which such person may be`
  line `lawfully transferred for care and treatment therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that transfer of a prisoner with mental illness to the psychiatric ward in the medical wing of`
  line `the prison shall be sufficient to meet the requirements under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where there is no provision for a psychiatric ward in the medical wing, the`
  line `prisoner may be transferred to a mental health establishment with prior permission of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The method, modalities and procedure by which the transfer of a prisoner under this section is to`
  line `be effected shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The medical officer of a prison or jail shall send a quarterly report to the concerned Board`
  line `certifying therein that there are no prisoners with mental illness in the prison or jail.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may visit the prison or jail and ask the medical officer as to why the prisoner with`
  line `mental illness, if any, has been kept in the prison or jail and not transferred for treatment to a mental`
  line `health establishment.`
  line
  line `(5) The medical officer in-charge of a mental health establishment wherein any person referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) is detained, shall once in every six months, make a special report regarding the mental`
  line `and physical condition of such person to the authority under whose order such person is detained.`
  line
  line `(6) The appropriate Government shall setup mental health establishment in the medical wing of at`
  line `least one prison in each State and Union territory and prisoners with mental illness may ordinarily be`
  line `referred to and cared for in the said mental health establishment.`
  line
  line `(7) The mental health establishment setup under sub-section (5) shall be registered under this Act`
  line `with the Central or State Mental Health Authority, as the case may be, and shall conform to such`
  line `standards and procedures as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (6310)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Persons in custodial institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6310&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the person in-charge of a State run`
  line `custodial institution (including beggars homes, orphanages, women's protection homes and children`
  line `homes) that any resident of the institution has, or is likely to have, a mental illness, then, he shall take`
  line `such resident of the institution to the nearest mental health establishment run or funded by the`
  line `appropriate Government for assessment and treatment, as necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical officer in-charge of a mental health establishment shall be responsible for`
  line `assessment of the person with mental illness, and the treatment required by such persons shall be`
  line `decided in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (6311)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Question of mental illness in judicial process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6311&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `If during any judicial process before any`
  line `competent court, proof of mental illness is produced and is challenged by the other party, the court shall`
  line `refer the same for further scrutiny to the concerned Board and the Board shall, after examination of the`
  line `person alleged to have a mental illness either by itself or through a committee of experts, submit its`
  line `opinion to the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (6312)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Restriction to discharge functions by professionals not covered by profession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6312&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `No mental`
  line `health professional or medical practitioner shall discharge any duty or perform any function not`
  line `authorised by this Act or specify or recommend any medicine or treatment not authorised by the field of`
  line `his profession.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (6313)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Penalties for establishing or maintaining mental health establishment in contravention of provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6313&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever carries on a mental health establishment without registration shall`
  line `be liable to a penalty which shall not be less than five thousand rupees but which may extend to fifty`
  line `thousand rupees for first contravention or a penalty which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees`
  line `but which may extend to two lakh rupees for a second contravention or a penalty which shall not be less`
  line `than two lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees for every subsequent contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever knowingly serves in the capacity as a mental health professional in a mental health`
  line `establishment which is not registered under this Act, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the penalty under this section shall be adjudicated by the`
  line `State Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever fails to pay the amount of penalty, the State Authority may forward the order to the`
  line `Collector of the district in which such person owns any property or resides or carries on his business or`
  line `profession or where the mental health establishment is situated, and the Collector shall recover from`
  line `such persons or mental health establishment the amount specified thereunder, as if it were an arrear of`
  line `land revenue.`
  line
  line `(5) All sums realised by way of penalties under this Chapter shall be credited to the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (6314)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Punishment for contravention of provisions of the Act or rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6314&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, or of any rule or`
  line `regulation made thereunder shall for first contravention be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both,`
  line `and for any subsequent contravention with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (6315)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6315&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (6316)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6316&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by a general or special`
  line `order, call upon the Authority or the Board to furnish, periodically or as and when required any`
  line `information concerning the activities carried on by the Authority or the Board, as the case may be, in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed, to enable that Government, to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by a general or special order, call upon the State Authority or the`
  line `Board to furnish, periodically or as and when required any information concerning the activities carried`
  line `on by the State Authority or the Board in such form as may be prescribed, to enable that Government, to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (6332)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6332&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy, other than those relating to technical`
  line `and administrative matters, as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (6333)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Central Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6333&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the`
  line `Central Government is of the opinion---`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Central Authority, it is unable to`
  line `discharge the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Central Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by`
  line `the Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification and for reasons to be specified therein, supersede the`
  line `Central Authority for such period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Central Authority to make representations against the proposed supersession and shall`
  line `consider representations, if any, of the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1), superseding the Central`
  line Authority,---
  line
  line `(a) the chairperson and other members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices`
  line `as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Central Authority shall, until the Central Authority is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the Central Government or such`
  line `authority as the Central Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the Central Authority shall, until the Central Authority is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government shall reconstitute the Central Authority by a fresh appointment`
  line `of its chairperson and other members and in such case any person who had vacated his office under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report`
  line `of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (6334)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Power of State Government to supersede State Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6334&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the State`
  line `Government is of the opinion---`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of circumstances beyond the control of the State Authority, it is unable to`
  line `discharge the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the State Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by`
  line `the State Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the State Government may, by notification and for reasons to be specified therein, supersede the State`
  line `Authority for such period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the State Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the State Authority to make representations against the proposed supersession and shall`
  line `consider representations, if any, of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the State Authority,---`
  line
  line `(a) the chairperson and other members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices`
  line `as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the State Authority shall, until the State Authority is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the State Government or such`
  line `authority as the State Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the State Authority shall, until the State Authority is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), vest in the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the State Government shall reconstitute the State Authority by a fresh appointment of its`
  line `chairperson and other members and in such case any person who had vacated his office under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before the`
  line `State Legislature at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (6335)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Special provisions for States in north-east and hill States`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6335&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, the provisions of this Act shall, taking into consideration the communication,`
  line `travel and transportation difficulties, apply to the States of Assam, Meghalaya, Tripura, Mizoram,`
  line `Manipur, Nagaland, Arunachal Pradesh and Sikkim, with following modifications, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) under sub-section (3) of section 73, the chairperson of the Central Authority may constitute`
  line `one or more Boards for all the States;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2) of section 80, reference to the period of "seven days", and in sub-section (3)`
  line `of that section, reference to the period of "twenty-one" days shall be construed as "ten days" and`
  line `"thirty days", respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (9) of section 87, reference to the period of "seventy-two hours" shall be`
  line `construed as "one hundred twenty hours", and in sub-sections (3) and (12) of that section, reference`
  line `to a period of "seven days" shall be construed as ten days;`
  line
  line `(d) in sub-section (3) of section 88, reference to the period of "twenty-four hours" shall be`
  line `construed as "seventy-two hours";`
  line
  line `(e) in clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (9) of section 89, reference to the period of "three days"`
  line `and "seven days" shall be construed as "seven days" and "ten days" respectively;`
  line
  line `(f) in sub-section (3) of section 90, reference to the period of "seven days" and in sub-section (4)`
  line `of that section, reference to the period of "twenty-one days" shall be construed as "ten days" and`
  line `"thirty days" respectively;`
  line
  line `(g) in sub-section (4) of section 94, reference to the period of "seventy-two hours" shall be`
  line `construed as "one hundred twenty hours".`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of clauses (b) to (g) of sub-section (1) shall also apply to the States of`
  line `Uttarakhand, Himachal Pradesh and Jammu and Kashmir* and the Union territories of Lakshadweep and`
  line `Andaman and Nicobar Islands.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall cease to have effect on the expiry of a period of ten years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act, except as respects things done or omitted to be done before such`
  line `cesser, and upon such cesser section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply as if`
  line `this Act had then been repealed by a Central Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (6336)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Presumption of severe stress in case of attempt to commit suicide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6336&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 309 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) any person who attempts to`
  line `commit suicide shall be presumed, unless proved otherwise, to have severe stress and shall not be tried`
  line `and punished under the said Code.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall have a duty to provide care, treatment and rehabilitation to a`
  line `person, having severe stress and who attempted to commit suicide, to reduce the risk of recurrence of`
  line `attempt to commit suicide.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (6337)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6337&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding`
  line `in respect of any matter which the Authority or the Board is empowered by or under this Act to`
  line `determine, and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action`
  line `taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (6338)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Transitory provisions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6338&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, if it considers so necessary in the`
  line `interest of persons with mental illness being governed by the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987),`
  line `take appropriate interim measures by making necessary transitory schemes.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (6339)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Chairperson, members and staff of Authority and Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6339&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line The
  line `chairperson, and other members and the officers and other employees of the Authority and Board shall`
  line `be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (6340)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6340&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the appropriate Government or against the chairperson or any other member of the Authority`
  line `or the Board, as the case may be, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder in the discharge of official duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (6341)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Act to have overriding effect`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6341&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have overriding effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force`
  line `or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (6342)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of Central Government and State Governments to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6342&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the State Government may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first rules shall be made by the Central Government, by notification.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under`
  line `sub-section (1) may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) qualifications relating to clinical psychologist under sub-clause (ii) of clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) qualifications relating to psychiatric social worker under clause (w) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of nomination of members of the Central Authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(d) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `chairperson and other members of the Central Authority under sub-section (3) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure for registration (including the fees to be levied for such registration) of the`
  line `mental health establishments under sub-section (2) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of nomination of members of the State Authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(g) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `chairperson and other members of the State Authority under sub-section (3) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for registration (including the fees to be levied for such registration) of the`
  line `mental health establishments under sub-section (2) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of accounts and other relevant records and annual statement of accounts under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 59;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in, and the time within which, an annual report shall be prepared under section 60;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of accounts and other relevant records and annual statement of accounts under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 63;`
  line
  line `(l) the form in, and the time within which, an annual report shall be prepared under section 64;`
  line
  line `(m) manner of constitution of the Board by the State Authority for a district or groups of districts`
  line `in a State;`
  line
  line `(n) other disqualifications of chairperson or members of the Board under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 82;`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by rules or in respect for which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(4) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under`
  line `sub-section (2) may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of proof of mental healthcare and treatment under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) provision of half-way homes, sheltered accommodation and supported accommodation under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(c) hospitals and community based rehabilitation establishment and services under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(d) basic medical records of which access is to be given to a person with mental illness under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(e) custodial institutions under sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(f) the form of application to be submitted by the mental health establishment with the`
  line `undertaking that the mental health establishment fulfils the minimum standards, if any, specified by`
  line `the Authority, under the Explanation to sub-section (2) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of certificate of registration under sub-section (3) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of application, the details, the fees to be accompanied with it under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 66;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of certificate of provisional registration containing particulars and information under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(j) the fees for renewal of registration under sub-section (11) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(k) the person or persons (including representatives of the local community) for the purpose of`
  line `conducting an audit of the registered mental health establishments under sub-section (1) and fees to`
  line `be charged by the Authority for conducting such audit under sub-section (2) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(l) the person or persons for the purpose of conducting and inspection or inquiry of the mental`
  line `health establishments under sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner to enter and search of a mental health establishment operating without registration`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(n) the fees for issuing a duplicate certificate under sub-section (2) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner in which the Authority shall maintain in digital format a register of`
  line `mental health establishments, the particulars of the certificate of registration so granted in a separate`
  line `register to be maintained under section 71;`
  line
  line `(p) constitution of the Boards under sub-section (3) of section 73;`
  line
  line `(q) the honorarium and other allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of, the chairperson and members of the Board under sub-section (3) of section 75;`
  line
  line `(r) method, modalities and procedure for transfer of prisoners under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 103;`
  line
  line `(s) the standard and procedure to which the Central or State Health Authority shall confirm under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 103;`
  line
  line `(t) the form for furnishing periodical information under section 110; and`
  line
  line `(u) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by rules or in respect for which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (6343)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Power of Central Authority to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6343&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority may, by`
  line `notification, make regulations, consistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder,`
  line `to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) manner of making an advance directive under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) additional regulations, regarding the procedure of advance directive to protect the rights of`
  line `persons with mental illness under sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `(including the qualifications, experience and manner of appointment) of, the chief executive officer`
  line `and other officers and employees of the Central Authority under sub-section (3) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(d) the times and places of meetings of the Central Authority and rules of procedure in regard to`
  line `the transaction of business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 44;`
  line
  line `(e) the minimum standards of facilities and services under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 65;`
  line
  line `(f) the minimum qualifications for the personnel engaged in mental health establishment under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(g) provisions for maintenance of records and reporting under clause (c) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 65;`
  line
  line `(h) any other conditions under clause (d) of sub-section (4) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(i) categories of different mental health establishment under clause (a) of sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 65;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of application to be made by the mental health establishment and the fees to be`
  line `accompanied with it under sub-section (12) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(k) manner of submitting evidence under sub-section (13) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of filing objections under sub-section (14) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(m) the time and places and rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings to be observed by the Central Authority and the Board under section 87;`
  line
  line `(n) regulations under sub-section (2) of section 96 and under sub-section (8) of section 97;`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (6344)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Power of State Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6344&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority may, by notification,`
  line `make regulations, consistent with the provision of this Act and the rules made thereunder, to carry out`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum quality standards of mental health services under sub-section (9) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(b) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `(including the qualifications, experience and manner of appointment) of the chief executive officer`
  line `and other officers and employees of the State Authority under sub-section (3) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the State Authority shall publish the list of registered mental health`
  line `professionals under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(d) the times and places of meetings of the State Authority and rules of procedure in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 56;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of application to be made by the mental health establishment and the fees to be`
  line `accompanied with it under sub-section (12) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of filing objections under sub-section (14) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (6345)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Laying of rules and regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6345&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made by the Central Government and every`
  line `regulation made by the Central Authority under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or regulation, as the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule or`
  line `regulation, as the case may be, should not be made, the rule or regulation, as the case may be, shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or regulation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the State Government and every regulation made by the State Authority`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of the State`
  line `Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature consists of one House, before`
  line `that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (6346)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6346&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary or expedient`
  line `for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (6347)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Repeal and saving`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874&sectionId=6347&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00024_201710_1517807327874
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken (including any`
  line `rule, notification, inspection, order or declaration made or any document or instrument executed or`
  line `any direction given or any proceedings taken or any penalty or fine imposed) under the repealed Act`
  line `shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done`
  line `or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Authority for Mental Health Services, and the State Authority for Mental Health`
  line `Services established under the repealed Act shall, continue to function under the corresponding`
  line `provisions of this Act, unless and until the Central Authority and the State Authority are constituted`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any person appointed in the Central Authority for Mental Health Services, or the State`
  line `Authority for Mental Health Services or any person appointed as the visitor under the repealed Act`
  line `and holding office as such immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall, on such`
  line `commencement continue to hold their respective offices under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line `Act, unless they are removed or until superannuated;`
  line
  line `(d) any person appointed under the provisions of the repealed Act and holding office as such`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall, on such commencement continue to hold`
  line `his office under the corresponding provisions of this Act, unless they are removed or until`
  line superannuated;
  line
  line `(e) any licence granted under the provisions of the repealed Act, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `granted under the corresponding provisions of this Act unless the same are cancelled or modified`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) any proceeding pending in any court under the repealed Act on the commencement of this Act`
  line `may be continued in that court as if this Act had not been enacted;`
  line
  line `(g) any appeal preferred from the order of a Magistrate under the repealed Act but not disposed of`
  line `before the commencement of this Act may be disposed of by the court as if this Act had not been`
  line enacted.
  line
  line `(3) The mention of the particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect`
  line `of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
